  ('36514', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to nominate CPT code 36514 (therapeutic apheresis; for plasma pheresis) as potentially misvalued; the current direct PE inputs, including the L056A (RN/OCN) clinical labor code and the 50 percent equipment utilization rate for the cell separator system (EQ084), are retained."}', 'our proposal not to nominate this code as potentially misvalued.'),
  ('37254', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the proposed (RUC-recommended) work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 37254, part of the new 46-code lower extremity revascularization (LER) family (37254-37299) replacing CPT codes 37220-37235."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing the proposed work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the LER family, with the previously mentioned increase to two drug-coated balloon (SD382) supplies for CPT codes 37263, 37265, 37271, and 37273 as well as two drug eluting tibial stent (SD379) supplies for CPT codes 37286, 37287, 37294 and 37295.'),
