  ('37296', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the proposed (RUC-recommended) work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 37296, part of the new 46-code lower extremity revascularization (LER) family (37254-37299) replacing CPT codes 37220-37235."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing the proposed work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the LER family, with the previously mentioned increase to two drug-coated balloon (SD382) supplies for CPT codes 37263, 37265, 37271, and 37273 as well as two drug eluting tibial stent (SD379) supplies for CPT codes 37286, 37287, 37294 and 37295.'),
  ('37297', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the proposed (RUC-recommended) work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 37297, part of the new 46-code lower extremity revascularization (LER) family (37254-37299) replacing CPT codes 37220-37235."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing the proposed work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the LER family, with the previously mentioned increase to two drug-coated balloon (SD382) supplies for CPT codes 37263, 37265, 37271, and 37273 as well as two drug eluting tibial stent (SD379) supplies for CPT codes 37286, 37287, 37294 and 37295.'),
  ('37298', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the proposed (RUC-recommended) work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 37298, part of the new 46-code lower extremity revascularization (LER) family (37254-37299) replacing CPT codes 37220-37235."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing the proposed work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the LER family, with the previously mentioned increase to two drug-coated balloon (SD382) supplies for CPT codes 37263, 37265, 37271, and 37273 as well as two drug eluting tibial stent (SD379) supplies for CPT codes 37286, 37287, 37294 and 37295.'),
  ('37299', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the proposed (RUC-recommended) work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 37299, part of the new 46-code lower extremity revascularization (LER) family (37254-37299) replacing CPT codes 37220-37235."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing the proposed work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the LER family, with the previously mentioned increase to two drug-coated balloon (SD382) supplies for CPT codes 37263, 37265, 37271, and 37273 as well as two drug eluting tibial stent (SD379) supplies for CPT codes 37286, 37287, 37294 and 37295.'),
  ('38225', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 38225 (CAR-T therapy; harvesting of blood-derived T lymphocytes) is not paid separately under the PFS. CMS finalized continuation of bundling this manufacturing/preparatory step into the payment for the CAR-T product itself."}', 'policy to continue to bundle payment under the PFS for CAR-T services described under CPT codes 38225, 38226, and 38227.'),
  ('38226', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 38226 (CAR-T therapy; preparation of blood-derived T lymphocytes for transportation, e.g. cryopreservation, storage) is not paid separately under the PFS. CMS finalized continuation of bundling this manufacturing step into the payment for the CAR-T product itself."}', 'policy to continue to bundle payment under the PFS for CAR-T services described under CPT codes 38225, 38226, and 38227.'),
  ('38227', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 38227 (CAR-T therapy; receipt and preparation of CAR-T cells for administration) is not paid separately under the PFS. CMS finalized continuation of bundling this manufacturing step into the payment for the CAR-T product itself."}', 'policy to continue to bundle payment under the PFS for CAR-T services described under CPT codes 38225, 38226, and 38227.'),
  ('38228', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 38228 (the service of CAR T-cell therapy administration, autologous) is paid separately under the PFS, aligning with OPPS policy. Unlike the bundled manufacturing-step codes 38225-38227, the administration service is separately recognized and payable."}', 'we also finalized to pay separately for CPT code 38228 (the service of CAR T-cell therapy administration),'),
  ('38228', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized changing the PC/TC indicator for CPT 38228 (CAR-T cell administration, autologous) from \"5\" (incident to) to \"0\" for CY 2026, agreeing that the incident-to designation was an unintended technical error since the physician personally supervises initiation of the product infusion; this aligns 38228 with similar services such as CPT 38240 and 38242."}', 'We are therefore finalizing a change in the PC/TC indicator for CPT code 38228 from ``5'''' to ``0'''' for CY 2026.'),
  ('43889', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized a work RVU of 12.56 for CPT code 43889 (endoscopic sleeve gastroplasty), applying the 23-hour policy in its entirety (reducing the RUC crosswalk value of 13.50), along with RUC-recommended direct PE inputs without refinement."}', 'After reviewing the public comments, we are finalizing the work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 43889 as proposed.'),
  ('47384', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized a work RVU of 9.41 for CPT code 47384 (irreversible electroporation ablation, liver tumors, percutaneous) with direct PE refined to the standard 000/010 global day pre-service clinical labor times in the facility setting, since it is a 0-day global procedure."}', 'we are proposing the RUC-recommended work RVUs of 9.41 for CPT code 47384 and 13.50 for CPT code 55877.'),
  ('47538', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 47538 is cited by CMS as a code with approximately 90 percent of its valuation based in practice expense that carries a Multiple Procedure (MPPR) indicator of \"2\", meaning payment is generally 100 percent of the highest valued procedure and 50 percent of the fee schedule amount for remaining billed procedures."}', 'which follow this pattern while also having a Multiple Procedure indicator of ``2'''' (such as CPT codes 19105, 27278, 33285, 47538, 55874, and HCPCS codes 0446T and 0448T).'),
  ('52443', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 3.62 for CPT 52443 (cystourethroscopy with balloon dilation of prostatic urethra), rejecting requests for 4.50 to 8.50. Direct PE inputs were finalized as proposed except CMS finalized the RUC-recommended 5 minutes for clinical activity CA023 (post-procedure monitoring) and inclusion of a single SM021 sanitizing cloth-wipe supply."}', 'After consideration of the public comments, we are finalizing the RUC-recommended work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 52443 as proposed with the following exceptions where we are finalizing the following RUC recommended direct PE inputs: 5 minutes for CA023 and the inclusion of a single SM021 supply.'),
  ('52500', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 6.00 for CPT code 52500 (transurethral resection of bladder neck); the Transurethral Robotic-assisted Resection of Prostate family was finalized as proposed."}', 'We proposed the RUC-recommended work RVU of 6.00 for CPT code 52500, the work RVU of 10.25 for CPT code 52597, the work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 52601, the work RVU of 6.55 for CPT code 52630, and the work RVU of 10.05 for CPT code 52648.'),
  ('52597', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 10.25 for CPT code 52597 (transurethral robotic-assisted waterjet resection of prostate); the Transurethral Robotic-assisted Resection of Prostate family was finalized as proposed."}', 'We proposed the RUC-recommended work RVU of 6.00 for CPT code 52500, the work RVU of 10.25 for CPT code 52597, the work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 52601, the work RVU of 6.55 for CPT code 52630, and the work RVU of 10.05 for CPT code 52648.'),
  ('52601', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 52601 (transurethral electrosurgical resection of prostate (TURP); a decrease from the current 13.16); the Transurethral Robotic-assisted Resection of Prostate family was finalized as proposed."}', 'We proposed the RUC-recommended work RVU of 6.00 for CPT code 52500, the work RVU of 10.25 for CPT code 52597, the work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 52601, the work RVU of 6.55 for CPT code 52630, and the work RVU of 10.05 for CPT code 52648.'),
  ('52630', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 6.55 for CPT code 52630 (transurethral resection of residual/regrowth obstructive prostate tissue); the Transurethral Robotic-assisted Resection of Prostate family was finalized as proposed."}', 'We proposed the RUC-recommended work RVU of 6.00 for CPT code 52500, the work RVU of 10.25 for CPT code 52597, the work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 52601, the work RVU of 6.55 for CPT code 52630, and the work RVU of 10.05 for CPT code 52648.'),
  ('52648', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 10.05 for CPT code 52648 (laser vaporization of prostate, with direct PE refinements removing 6 minutes of CA021 clinical labor and the non-facility biopsy specimen cup supply); the Transurethral Robotic-assisted Resection of Prostate family was finalized as proposed."}', 'We proposed the RUC-recommended work RVU of 6.00 for CPT code 52500, the work RVU of 10.25 for CPT code 52597, the work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 52601, the work RVU of 6.55 for CPT code 52630, and the work RVU of 10.05 for CPT code 52648.'),
  ('52649', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized a work RVU of 13.00 for CPT code 52649 (laser enucleation of prostate with morcellation) based on a crosswalk to CPT code 53500, rejecting the RUC-recommended 14.56 due to decreased surveyed intraservice time (120 to 90 minutes)."}', 'continue to believe that the proposed work RVU of 13.00 is the most accurate valuation for CPT code 52649'),
  ('55705', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.93 for CPT 55705 (prostate biopsy, any approach, non-imaging-guided) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55706', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 4.27 for CPT 55706 (transperineal stereotactic template guided saturation prostate biopsies) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55707', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 2.63 for CPT 55707 (transrectal ultrasound-guided (sextant) prostate biopsy, ultrasound-localized) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55708', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 3.39 for CPT 55708 (transrectal ultrasound-guided (sextant) prostate biopsy with MRI-fusion guidance) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55709', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 3.23 for CPT 55709 (transperineal ultrasound-guided (sextant) prostate biopsy, ultrasound-localized) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55710', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 3.81 for CPT 55710 (transperineal ultrasound-guided (sextant) prostate biopsy with MRI-fusion guidance) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55711', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 2.61 for CPT 55711 (transrectal MRI-ultrasound-fusion guided prostate biopsy, targeted lesion(s) only) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55712', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 3.10 for CPT 55712 (transperineal MRI-ultrasound-fusion guided prostate biopsy, first targeted lesion) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55713', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 4.00 for CPT 55713 (in-bore CT- or MRI-guided (sextant) prostate biopsy with biopsy of additional targeted lesion(s)) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55714', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 3.62 for CPT 55714 (in-bore CT- or MRI-guided prostate biopsy, targeted lesion(s) only, first targeted lesion) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55715', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.05 for CPT 55715 (each additional MRI-ultrasound fusion or in-bore CT/MRI-guided targeted lesion prostate biopsy (add-on code)) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('55840', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 21.36 for CPT 55840 (prostatectomy, retropubic radical, with or without nerve sparing) as proposed, with direct PE inputs finalized for the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy code family."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy family as proposed.'),
  ('55842', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 21.36 for CPT 55842 (retropubic radical prostatectomy with limited pelvic lymphadenectomy) as proposed, with direct PE inputs finalized for the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy code family."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy family as proposed.'),
  ('55845', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 25.18 for CPT 55845 (retropubic radical prostatectomy with bilateral pelvic lymphadenectomy) as proposed, with direct PE inputs finalized for the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy code family."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy family as proposed.'),
  ('55866', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 22.46 for CPT 55866 (laparoscopic/robotic retropubic radical prostatectomy) as proposed, with direct PE inputs finalized for the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy code family."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy family as proposed.'),
  ('55867', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 19.53 for CPT 55867 (laparoscopic/robotic simple subtotal prostatectomy; CMS also finalized a correction reducing CA039 post-operative visit clinical labor to one Level 3 and one Level 4 office visit (89 minutes)) as proposed, with direct PE inputs finalized for the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy code family."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy family as proposed.'),
  ('55868', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 22.46 for CPT 55868 (laparoscopic radical prostatectomy with lymph node biopsy(ies) (limited pelvic lymphadenectomy)) as proposed, with direct PE inputs finalized for the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy code family."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy family as proposed.'),
  ('55869', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 27.41 for CPT 55869 (laparoscopic radical prostatectomy with bilateral pelvic lymphadenectomy) as proposed, based on a crosswalk to CPT 50543 and rejecting the RUC-recommended 29.35, which CMS found anomalously high (30-40 percent more intense than peer codes)."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Laparoscopic Prostatectomy family as proposed.'),
  ('55874', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 55874 is cited by CMS as a code with approximately 90 percent of its valuation based in practice expense that carries a Multiple Procedure (MPPR) indicator of \"2\", meaning payment is generally 100 percent of the highest valued procedure and 50 percent of the fee schedule amount for remaining billed procedures."}', 'which follow this pattern while also having a Multiple Procedure indicator of ``2'''' (such as CPT codes 19105, 27278, 33285, 47538, 55874, and HCPCS codes 0446T and 0448T).'),
  ('55877', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized a work RVU of 13.50 and RUC-recommended direct PE inputs without refinement for CPT code 55877 (irreversible electroporation ablation, prostate tumors, percutaneous)."}', 'we are proposing the RUC-recommended work RVUs of 9.41 for CPT code 47384 and 13.50 for CPT code 55877.'),
  ('61624', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 20.00 for CPT 61624 (transcatheter permanent occlusion or embolization, central nervous system), abandoning its proposed 17.06 crosswalk to CPT 49622 after agreeing with commenters that the crosswalk undervalued this complex neurointerventional procedure."}', 'recommended work RVUs of 20.00 for CPT code 61624 and 15.31 for CPT code 61626, as well as work RVUs of 2.25 for CPT code 75894 and 1.85 for CPT code 75898.'),
  ('61626', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 15.31 for CPT 61626 (transcatheter embolization, non-CNS head or neck), rejecting its proposed 13.46. CMS also finalized 5 minutes of CA011 (education/consent) clinical labor, removal of supply SD172 (cerebral guidewire), and addition of a second SD089 hydrophobic guidewire for this code."}', 'recommended work RVUs of 20.00 for CPT code 61624 and 15.31 for CPT code 61626, as well as work RVUs of 2.25 for CPT code 75894 and 1.85 for CPT code 75898.'),
  ('61715', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized maintaining facility pricing and the PC/TC coding structure (with contractor pricing for global and technical components) for CPT 61715 (MRgFUS intracranial ablation), declining to set non-facility pricing due to insufficient data. CPT 61715 is also added to the low volume services list with an expected specialty assignment of Neurosurgery."}', 'we did not receive enough information about typical non-facility direct PE inputs or reasonable crosswalk codes to finalize non-facility pricing for CPT code 61715 for CY 2026, therefore we are finalizing to maintain the facility pricing and coding structure for CPT code 61715 as proposed. We are also finalizing the addition of this code to the low volume services list with an expected specialty assignment of Neurosurgery'),
  ('62287', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 62287 (percutaneous needle-based decompression of nucleus pulposus of intervertebral disc, lumbar) will remain in active use for CY 2026. The CPT Editorial Panel removed it from the deletion list and revised its descriptor, and CMS will update its ratesetting files accordingly rather than deleting the code or removing its RVUs."}', 'the CPT Editorial Panel later removed CPT code 62287 from the deletion list and instead revised its descriptor. We will update our ratesetting files accordingly to indicate that CPT code 62287 will remain in active use for CY 2026.'),
  ('62330', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 8.00 for CPT 62330 (percutaneous interlaminar lumbar decompression, one interspace) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs without refinement."}', 'work RVU values for the Percutaneous Interlaminar Lumbar Decompression code family (CPT codes 62330 and 62331) as proposed.'),
  ('62331', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 4.25 for CPT 62331 (percutaneous interlaminar lumbar decompression, additional interspace(s), add-on code) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs without refinement."}', 'work RVU values for the Percutaneous Interlaminar Lumbar Decompression code family (CPT codes 62330 and 62331) as proposed.'),
  ('63032', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 2.50 for CPT 63032 (add-on code for laminotomy with repair of annular defect by implantation of bone anchored annular closure device) as proposed, with no direct PE inputs for this code."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVU of 2.50 for CPT code 63032 as proposed. We proposed and we are finalizing no direct PE inputs for this code.'),
  ('64567', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.50 for CPT 64567 (percutaneous electrical nerve field stimulation, cranial nerves, without implantation) and the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs as proposed."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 64567 as proposed.'),
  ('64654', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 11.00 for CPT 64654 (initial open implantation of baroreflex activation therapy (BAT) modulation system) as proposed, with the direct PE inputs as recommended by the RUC."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs for all of the codes in the Baroreflex Activation Therapy family'),
  ('64655', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 11.30 for CPT 64655 (revision or replacement of BAT modulation system, lead only) as proposed, with the direct PE inputs as recommended by the RUC."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs for all of the codes in the Baroreflex Activation Therapy family'),
  ('64656', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 8.01 for CPT 64656 (revision or replacement of BAT modulation system, pulse generator only) as proposed, with the direct PE inputs as recommended by the RUC."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs for all of the codes in the Baroreflex Activation Therapy family'),
  ('64657', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 12.13 for CPT 64657 (removal of BAT modulation system, total system) as proposed, with the direct PE inputs as recommended by the RUC."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs for all of the codes in the Baroreflex Activation Therapy family'),
  ('64658', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 8.95 for CPT 64658 (removal of BAT modulation system, lead only) as proposed, with the direct PE inputs as recommended by the RUC."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs for all of the codes in the Baroreflex Activation Therapy family'),
  ('64659', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 8.23 for CPT 64659 (removal of BAT modulation system, pulse generator only) as proposed, with the direct PE inputs as recommended by the RUC."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs for all of the codes in the Baroreflex Activation Therapy family'),
  ('64728', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 2.70 for CPT 64728 (percutaneous median nerve decompression at carpal tunnel with balloon dilation, including ultrasound guidance) and the direct PE inputs as proposed, rejecting commenter requests for a work RVU of 6.00 as anomalously intense."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 64728 as proposed.'),
  ('65780', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized a technical correction for CPT 65780 (ocular surface reconstruction; amniotic membrane transplantation, multiple layers): the intraservice work time is corrected from the erroneously listed 25 minutes to the intended 35 minutes for CY 2026. The total work time of 192 minutes was listed correctly and is unchanged."}', 'work time of 25 minutes; we proposed to correct this to the intended work time of 35 minutes. We note that the total work time of 192 minutes was listed correctly for CPT code 65780 and does not require a technical correction.'),
  ('70471', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 2.50 for CPT 70471 (CT angiography, head and neck, with contrast) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, for the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck code family."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck family as proposed.'),
  ('70471', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CPT code 70471 is added to the list of codes subject to the OPPS cap: the technical component of the PFS payment amount (prior to geographic adjustment) is capped at the OPPS payment amount for the service. CMS finalized the addition as proposed."}', '70471 (Computed tomographic angiography (CTA), head and neck, with contrast material(s), including noncontrast images, when performed, and image postprocessing)'),
  ('70472', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.77 for CPT 70472 (CT cerebral perfusion analysis with concurrent CT or CTA (add-on code)) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, for the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck code family."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck family as proposed.'),
  ('70472', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CPT code 70472 is added to the list of codes subject to the OPPS cap: the technical component of the PFS payment amount (prior to geographic adjustment) is capped at the OPPS payment amount for the service. CMS finalized the addition as proposed."}', '70472 (Computed tomographic (CT) cerebral perfusion analysis with contrast material(s), including image postprocessing performed with concurrent CT or CT angiography of the same anatomy'),
  ('70473', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.00 for CPT 70473 (CT cerebral perfusion analysis without concurrent CT or CTA) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, for the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck code family."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck family as proposed.'),
  ('70473', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CPT code 70473 is added to the list of codes subject to the OPPS cap: the technical component of the PFS payment amount (prior to geographic adjustment) is capped at the OPPS payment amount for the service. CMS finalized the addition as proposed."}', '70473 (Computed tomographic (CT) cerebral perfusion analysis with contrast material(s), including image postprocessing performed without concurrent CT or CT angiography of the same anatomy)'),
  ('70496', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.75 for CPT 70496 (CT angiography, head, with contrast) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, for the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck code family."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck family as proposed.'),
  ('70498', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.75 for CPT 70498 (CT angiography, neck, with contrast) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, for the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck code family."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Cerebral Perfusion & CT Angiography-Head & Neck family as proposed.'),
  ('75577', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 0.85 for CPT 75577 (quantification and characterization of coronary atherosclerotic plaque from coronary CTA) and finalized crosswalking its PE RVU to CPT 77373, recognizing resource costs including the vendor per-patient fee of $1500 for plaque analysis software."}', 'we are finalizing our policies for CPT code 75577 as proposed.'),
  ('75894', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 2.25 for CPT 75894 (transcatheter embolization, radiological supervision and interpretation), and finalized the direct PE inputs including 60 minutes of CA021 clinical staff time."}', 'recommended work RVUs of 20.00 for CPT code 61624 and 15.31 for CPT code 61626, as well as work RVUs of 2.25 for CPT code 75894 and 1.85 for CPT code 75898.'),
  ('75898', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.85 for CPT 75898 (angiography through existing catheter for follow-up study), and finalized the direct PE inputs including 45 minutes of CA021 clinical staff time."}', 'recommended work RVUs of 20.00 for CPT code 61624 and 15.31 for CPT code 61626, as well as work RVUs of 2.25 for CPT code 75894 and 1.85 for CPT code 75898.'),
  ('76017', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is not finalizing any changes to CPT 76017: it keeps its Multiple Procedure (MPPR) indicator of \"4\" and diagnostic imaging family indicator of \"88\", the standard assignments for MR procedures, rejecting commenter requests to make it modifier -51 exempt with an MPPR indicator of \"0\" and family indicator of \"99\"."}', 'We continue to believe that the indicators are appropriately assigned for CPT codes 76017, 76018, and 76019, which currently have a value of ``4'''' for the MPPR indicator and ``88'''' for the diagnostic imaging family'),
  ('76018', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is not finalizing any changes to CPT 76018: it keeps its Multiple Procedure (MPPR) indicator of \"4\" and diagnostic imaging family indicator of \"88\", the standard assignments for MR procedures, rejecting commenter requests to make it modifier -51 exempt with an MPPR indicator of \"0\" and family indicator of \"99\"."}', 'We continue to believe that the indicators are appropriately assigned for CPT codes 76017, 76018, and 76019, which currently have a value of ``4'''' for the MPPR indicator and ``88'''' for the diagnostic imaging family'),
  ('76019', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is not finalizing any changes to CPT 76019: it keeps its Multiple Procedure (MPPR) indicator of \"4\" and diagnostic imaging family indicator of \"88\", the standard assignments for MR procedures, rejecting commenter requests to make it modifier -51 exempt with an MPPR indicator of \"0\" and family indicator of \"99\"."}', 'We continue to believe that the indicators are appropriately assigned for CPT codes 76017, 76018, and 76019, which currently have a value of ``4'''' for the MPPR indicator and ``88'''' for the diagnostic imaging family'),
  ('76872', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.67 for CPT 76872 (transrectal ultrasound) as proposed, along with the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs, as part of the finalized Prostate Biopsy Services code family valuation."}', 'we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for the codes in the Prostate Biopsy Services family as proposed.'),
  ('77387', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS establishes the practice expense (PE) RVUs for radiation oncology treatment delivery CPT 77387 (with 77402, 77407, 77412, 77417) using the relationship between OPPS APC payment rates; CMS rejected an alternative approach based on hospital cost report direct-cost shares as imprecise."}', 'Oncology Treatment Delivery (CPT Codes 77387, 77402, 77407, 77412, and'),
  ('77402', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS establishes the practice expense (PE) RVUs for radiation oncology treatment delivery CPT 77402 (with 77387, 77407, 77412, 77417) using the relationship between OPPS APC payment rates; CMS rejected an alternative approach based on hospital cost report direct-cost shares as imprecise."}', 'Oncology Treatment Delivery (CPT Codes 77387, 77402, 77407, 77412, and'),
  ('77407', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS establishes the practice expense (PE) RVUs for radiation oncology treatment delivery CPT 77407 (with 77387, 77402, 77412, 77417) using the relationship between OPPS APC payment rates; CMS rejected an alternative approach based on hospital cost report direct-cost shares as imprecise."}', 'Oncology Treatment Delivery (CPT Codes 77387, 77402, 77407, 77412, and'),
  ('77412', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS establishes the practice expense (PE) RVUs for radiation oncology treatment delivery CPT 77412 (with 77387, 77402, 77407, 77417) using the relationship between OPPS APC payment rates; CMS rejected an alternative approach based on hospital cost report direct-cost shares as imprecise."}', 'Oncology Treatment Delivery (CPT Codes 77387, 77402, 77407, 77412, and'),
  ('77417', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS establishes the practice expense (PE) RVUs for radiation oncology treatment delivery CPT 77417 (with 77387, 77402, 77407, 77412) using the relationship between OPPS APC payment rates; CMS rejected an alternative approach based on hospital cost report direct-cost shares as imprecise."}', 'Oncology Treatment Delivery (CPT Codes 77387, 77402, 77407, 77412, and'),
  ('90480', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized maintaining procedure status X for CPT code 90480 (COVID-19 vaccine administration, first/only component), so it is not payable under the PFS; payment is addressed under previously finalized emergency-use-authorization policies. RVUs (RUC-recommended work RVU 0.25) will be displayed in Addendum B for display purposes only."}', 'We previously established CPT code 90480 with a procedure status of ``X'''' on the PFS, and the code is therefore not payable under the PFS.'),
  ('90481', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized assigning procedure status X to new add-on CPT code 90481 (each additional vaccine component administered with COVID-19 vaccine), so it is not payable under the PFS; CMS states 90481 is meant to be a tracking code only. Any RVUs will be published in Addendum B for display purposes only."}', 'We proposed to maintain procedure status ``X'''' for CPT code 90480 and assign procedure status ``X'''' to CPT code 90481.'),
  ('90482', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized assigning status indicator I (not valid for Medicare purposes) to CPT code 90482 (immunization counseling without administration, 3-10 minutes); Medicare instead pays for immunization counseling through E/M visit coding. RVUs will be displayed in Addendum B for display purposes only."}', 'The RUC requested that CMS delete HCPCS codes G0310-G0313, and replace them with the new CPT codes 90482, 90483, and 90484. However, we proposed to assign status indicator (``I'''') to each of these three services, as not valid for Medicare purposes.'),
  ('90483', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized assigning status indicator I (not valid for Medicare purposes) to CPT code 90483 (immunization counseling without administration, greater than 10 up to 20 minutes); Medicare instead pays for immunization counseling through E/M visit coding. RVUs will be displayed in Addendum B for display purposes only."}', 'The RUC requested that CMS delete HCPCS codes G0310-G0313, and replace them with the new CPT codes 90482, 90483, and 90484. However, we proposed to assign status indicator (``I'''') to each of these three services, as not valid for Medicare purposes.'),
  ('90484', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized assigning status indicator I (not valid for Medicare purposes) to CPT code 90484 (immunization counseling without administration, greater than 20 minutes); Medicare instead pays for immunization counseling through E/M visit coding. RVUs will be displayed in Addendum B for display purposes only."}', 'The RUC requested that CMS delete HCPCS codes G0310-G0313, and replace them with the new CPT codes 90482, 90483, and 90484. However, we proposed to assign status indicator (``I'''') to each of these three services, as not valid for Medicare purposes.'),
  ('90791', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that CPT code 90791 (Psychiatric diagnostic evaluation) may serve as an initiating visit for Community Health Integration (CHI) services, enabling CSWs, MFTs, and MHCs to bill Medicare directly for CHI services personally performed for the diagnosis or treatment of mental illness."}', 'proposal to allow CPT code 90791 (Psychiatric diagnostic evaluation) or'),
  ('90849', 'telehealth_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 90849 (Multiple-Family Group Psychotherapy) is added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List beginning in CY 2026, finalized as proposed after CMS found it meets steps 1-3 of the telehealth review process."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to add Multiple-Family Group Psychotherapy services (CPT code 90849) to the Medicare Telehealth Services List, beginning in CY 2026.'),
  ('90935', 'telehealth_allowed', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 90935 (hemodialysis procedure with single physician/QHP evaluation) is NOT added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List for CY 2026; CMS finalized as proposed because the service does not meet step 3 of the telehealth review process (not persuaded all service elements can be furnished via telehealth)."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to not add these services to the Medicare Telehealth Services List.'),
  ('90937', 'telehealth_allowed', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 90937 (hemodialysis procedure requiring repeated evaluations, with or without substantial revision of dialysis prescription) is NOT added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List for CY 2026; CMS finalized as proposed because the service does not meet step 3 of the telehealth review process."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to not add these services to the Medicare Telehealth Services List.'),
  ('90945', 'telehealth_allowed', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 90945 (dialysis procedure other than hemodialysis with single physician/QHP evaluation) is NOT added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List for CY 2026; CMS finalized as proposed because the service does not meet step 3 of the telehealth review process."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to not add these services to the Medicare Telehealth Services List.'),
  ('90947', 'telehealth_allowed', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 90947 (dialysis procedure other than hemodialysis requiring repeated evaluations) is NOT added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List for CY 2026; CMS finalized as proposed because the service does not meet step 3 of the telehealth review process."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to not add these services to the Medicare Telehealth Services List.'),
  ('91124', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 3.05 for new CPT code 91124 (rectal sensation, tone, and compliance study), with direct PE inputs finalized as proposed including 17 minutes of CA013 clinical labor time and 10 minutes of CA024 cleaning time; the SM015 enzymatic detergent supply is set at 8 ounces."}', 'Response: We appreciate the commenters for their support, and we are finalizing our proposed work RVUs for CPT code 91124 and 91125.'),
  ('91125', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 2.70 for new CPT code 91125 (anorectal manometry with rectal sensation and balloon expulsion test), and finalized 17 minutes of CA013 clinical labor time (revised upward from the proposed 2 minutes after comments) and 10 minutes of CA024 cleaning time."}', 'We are therefore finalizing 17 minutes of CA013 clinical labor time for CPT code 91125.'),
  ('92284', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized a work RVU of 0.29 for CPT code 92284 (diagnostic dark adaptation examination), rejecting the RUC-recommended 0.32, based on a crosswalk to CPT code 92132; the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs were finalized without refinement."}', 'After consideration of these comments, we are finalizing the work RVU and direct PE inputs for CPT code 92284 as proposed, along with finalizing the proposed non-covered status indicator for CPT code 92288.'),
  ('92288', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized assigning non-covered status indicator N to CPT code 92288 (screening dark adaptation measurement) because it is a screening service that has not been determined to be a preventive service under Section 1861 of the Social Security Act and is not covered under Medicare; RUC-recommended RVUs are listed for display purposes only."}', 'CPT code 92288 describes a screening service that has not been determined to be a preventive service under Section 1861 of the Social Security Act and as such is not covered under Medicare. We are proposing to assign status indicator (``N'''') to this service, as a non- covered service.'),
  ('92622', 'telehealth_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 92622 (diagnostic analysis, programming, and verification of an auditory osseointegrated sound processor, any type; first 60 minutes) is added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List beginning in CY 2026, finalized as proposed."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to add Auditory Osseointegrated Sound Processor services (CPT codes 92622 and 92623) to the Medicare Telehealth Services List, beginning in CY 2026.'),
  ('92623', 'telehealth_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 92623 (diagnostic analysis, programming, and verification of an auditory osseointegrated sound processor, any type; each additional 15 minutes) is added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List beginning in CY 2026, finalized as proposed."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to add Auditory Osseointegrated Sound Processor services (CPT codes 92622 and 92623) to the Medicare Telehealth Services List, beginning in CY 2026.'),
  ('92628', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 92628 (hearing device services) is assigned a non-payable status code under the CY 2026 PFS, finalized as proposed; section 1862(a)(7) of the Act prohibits Medicare payment under Part A or Part B for expenses incurred for hearing aids or examinations therefor."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing our proposal to assign non-payable status codes to each of the twelve new CPT codes in this family.'),
  ('92629', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 92629 (hearing device services) is assigned a non-payable status code under the CY 2026 PFS, finalized as proposed; section 1862(a)(7) of the Act prohibits Medicare payment under Part A or Part B for expenses incurred for hearing aids or examinations therefor."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing our proposal to assign non-payable status codes to each of the twelve new CPT codes in this family.'),
