  ('92920', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920 (percutaneous transluminal coronary angioplasty, single major coronary artery and/or branches); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs for all 12 codes in the Coronary Therapeutic Services and Procedures family as proposed.'),
  ('92924', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924 (percutaneous transluminal coronary atherectomy with angioplasty when performed); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('92928', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928 (percutaneous transcatheter placement of intracoronary stent(s), one lesion); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('92930', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930 (intracoronary stent placement, two or more distinct lesions or bifurcation lesion); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('92933', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933 (percutaneous transluminal coronary atherectomy with intracoronary stent); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('92937', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937 (percutaneous transluminal revascularization of or through coronary artery bypass graft, single vessel); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('92941', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941 (percutaneous transluminal revascularization of acute total/subtotal occlusion during acute myocardial infarction); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('92943', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943 (percutaneous transluminal revascularization of chronic total occlusion, antegrade approach); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('92945', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945 (percutaneous transluminal revascularization of chronic total occlusion, combined antegrade and retrograde approaches); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('92973', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.75 for add-on CPT code 92973 (percutaneous transluminal coronary thrombectomy, aspiration mechanical); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('93145', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized a work RVU of 0.65 for CPT 93145 (BAT interrogation device evaluation without programming) based on a crosswalk to CPT 93279, rejecting the RUC-recommended 0.79. CMS also withdrew its proposed clinical labor refinement and finalized the RUC-recommended RN (L051A) clinical labor type for this code."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs for all of the codes in the Baroreflex Activation Therapy family'),
  ('93146', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.90 for CPT 93146 (BAT interrogation device evaluation with programming) as proposed. CMS also withdrew its proposed clinical labor refinement and finalized the RUC-recommended RN (L051A) clinical labor type for this code."}', 'After consideration of the comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs for all of the codes in the Baroreflex Activation Therapy family'),
  ('93296', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized updates to the direct PE inputs for CPT code 93296 (remote interrogation device evaluation, up to 90 days): the clinical labor type changes from electrodiagnostic technician (L037A) to cardiovascular technician (L038B), and the equipment code changes from EQ320 (pacemaker interrogation system) to EQ198 (pacemaker follow-up system). The code was not designated as potentially misvalued."}', 'as suggested, and therefore, we are making these updates for CY 2026.'),
  ('93571', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.80 for add-on CPT code 93571 (intravascular Doppler velocity and/or pressure derived coronary flow reserve measurement, initial vessel); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('93572', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 1.44 for add-on CPT code 93572 (intravascular Doppler velocity and/or pressure derived coronary flow reserve measurement, each additional vessel); no direct PE inputs were finalized for this facility-based service."}', 'We proposed a work RVU of 8.35 for CPT code 92920, a work RVU of 10.13 for CPT code 92924, a work RVU of 10.00 for CPT code 92928, a work RVU of 11.94 for CPT code 92933, a work RVU of 11.30 for CPT code 92937, a work RVU of 12.72 for CPT code 92941, a work RVU of 13.69 for CPT code 92943, a work RVU of 1.75 for CPT code 92973, a work RVU of 12.00 for CPT code 92930, a work RVU of 15.00 for CPT code 92945, a work RVU of 1.80 for CPT code 93571, and a work RVU of 1.44 for CPT code 93572.'),
  ('95145', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to nominate CPT code 95145 (antigen preparation for allergen immunotherapy; single stinging insect venom) as potentially misvalued; current payment valuation is retained. CMS invited resubmission of the nomination with additional clarity for consideration in future rulemaking."}', 'finalizing our proposal not to nominate these codes as potentially'),
  ('95146', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to nominate CPT code 95146 (antigen preparation for allergen immunotherapy; 2 single stinging insect venoms) as potentially misvalued; current payment valuation is retained. CMS invited resubmission of the nomination with additional clarity for consideration in future rulemaking."}', 'finalizing our proposal not to nominate these codes as potentially'),
  ('95147', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to nominate CPT code 95147 (antigen preparation for allergen immunotherapy; 3 single stinging insect venoms) as potentially misvalued; current payment valuation is retained. CMS invited resubmission of the nomination with additional clarity for consideration in future rulemaking."}', 'finalizing our proposal not to nominate these codes as potentially'),
  ('95148', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to nominate CPT code 95148 (antigen preparation for allergen immunotherapy; 4 single stinging insect venoms) as potentially misvalued; current payment valuation is retained. CMS invited resubmission of the nomination with additional clarity for consideration in future rulemaking."}', 'finalizing our proposal not to nominate these codes as potentially'),
  ('95149', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to nominate CPT code 95149 (antigen preparation for allergen immunotherapy; 5 single stinging insect venoms) as potentially misvalued; current payment valuation is retained. CMS invited resubmission of the nomination with additional clarity for consideration in future rulemaking."}', 'finalizing our proposal not to nominate these codes as potentially'),
  ('95165', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized a CY 2026 price of $13.00 per mL for the multi-antigen supply (SH007) that is a direct practice expense input to CPT 95165 (professional services for supervision of preparation and provision of antigens for allergen immunotherapy), based on averaging submitted 50 mL invoices; this is a 45 percent increase over the previous $8.96 price, and CMS rejected the requested $17.07 price."}', 'pricing of $13.00 is a more accurate valuation for the SH007 supply.'),
  ('95800', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026 CMS finalized updated direct practice expense (PE) inputs for CPT 95800 (unattended home sleep study) to reflect the clinical shift from reusable to disposable home sleep apnea testing (HSAT) devices, as described in Table A-C3. CMS did not nominate the code as potentially misvalued."}', 'we are finalizing an update to the PE inputs as described in Table A-C3 for CY 2026.'),
  ('95970', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to designate CPT code 95970 (electronic analysis of implanted neurostimulator pulse generator/transmitter without programming) as potentially misvalued, concluding the current valuation of PE inputs remains appropriate and neurologists remain the dominant billing practitioner type."}', 'for CY 2026, we are finalizing our proposal not to designate these'),
  ('95976', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to designate CPT code 95976 (electronic analysis of implanted neurostimulator with simple cranial nerve programming) as potentially misvalued, concluding the current valuation of PE inputs remains appropriate and neurologists remain the dominant billing practitioner type."}', 'for CY 2026, we are finalizing our proposal not to designate these'),
  ('95977', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to designate CPT code 95977 (electronic analysis of implanted neurostimulator with complex cranial nerve programming) as potentially misvalued, concluding the current valuation of PE inputs remains appropriate and neurologists remain the dominant billing practitioner type."}', 'for CY 2026, we are finalizing our proposal not to designate these'),
  ('96156', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that Health Behavior Assessment and Intervention (HBAI) CPT code 96156 may serve as an initiating visit for Community Health Integration (CHI) services, alongside CPT codes 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167, 96168 and 90791."}', 'described by CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167, and'),
  ('96158', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that Health Behavior Assessment and Intervention (HBAI) CPT code 96158 may serve as an initiating visit for Community Health Integration (CHI) services, alongside CPT codes 96156, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167, 96168 and 90791."}', 'described by CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167, and'),
  ('96159', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that Health Behavior Assessment and Intervention (HBAI) CPT code 96159 may serve as an initiating visit for Community Health Integration (CHI) services, alongside CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96164, 96165, 96167, 96168 and 90791."}', 'described by CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167, and'),
  ('96160', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 96160 (administration of health risk assessment) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '96160 and 96161 (codes for administration of health risk'),
  ('96161', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 96161 (administration of health risk assessment) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '96160 and 96161 (codes for administration of health risk'),
  ('96164', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that Health Behavior Assessment and Intervention (HBAI) CPT code 96164 may serve as an initiating visit for Community Health Integration (CHI) services, alongside CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96165, 96167, 96168 and 90791."}', 'described by CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167, and'),
  ('96165', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that Health Behavior Assessment and Intervention (HBAI) CPT code 96165 may serve as an initiating visit for Community Health Integration (CHI) services, alongside CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96167, 96168 and 90791."}', 'described by CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167, and'),
  ('96167', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that Health Behavior Assessment and Intervention (HBAI) CPT code 96167 may serve as an initiating visit for Community Health Integration (CHI) services, alongside CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96168 and 90791."}', 'described by CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167, and'),
  ('96168', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that Health Behavior Assessment and Intervention (HBAI) CPT code 96168 may serve as an initiating visit for Community Health Integration (CHI) services, alongside CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167 and 90791."}', '96168 (and any subsequent HBAI codes) to serve as initiating visits for'),
  ('96202', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 96202 (caregiver behavior management training) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '96202 and 96203 (codes for caregiver behavior management'),
  ('96203', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 96203 (caregiver behavior management training) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '96202 and 96203 (codes for caregiver behavior management'),
  ('96380', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.28 and direct PE inputs for CPT code 96380 (administration of RSV monoclonal antibody, seasonal dose by intramuscular injection, with counseling); RVUs are displayed in Addendum B."}', 'After consideration of the public comments, we are finalizing the work RVUs and direct PE inputs for CPT codes 96380 and 96381 as proposed.'),
  ('96381', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.17 and direct PE inputs for CPT code 96381 (administration of RSV monoclonal antibody, seasonal dose by intramuscular injection, without counseling); RVUs are displayed in Addendum B."}', 'We proposed the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.28 for CPT code 96380 and 0.17 for CPT code 96381. We proposed the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs without refinement.'),
  ('96920', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to nominate CPT code 96920 (excimer laser treatment for psoriasis; total area less than 250 sq cm) as potentially misvalued. CMS declined to create an interim G-code for non-psoriasis indications and is making no changes to the code''s valuation at this time."}', 'CPT codes 96920, 92921, and 96922 as potentially misvalued.'),
  ('96921', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to nominate CPT code 96921 (excimer laser treatment for psoriasis; 250 sq cm to 500 sq cm) as potentially misvalued. CMS declined to create an interim G-code for non-psoriasis indications and is making no changes to the code''s valuation at this time."}', 'CPT codes 96920, 92921, and 96922 as potentially misvalued.'),
  ('96922', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized its proposal not to nominate CPT code 96922 (excimer laser treatment for psoriasis; over 500 sq cm) as potentially misvalued. CMS declined to create an interim G-code for non-psoriasis indications and is making no changes to the code''s valuation at this time."}', 'CPT codes 96920, 92921, and 96922 as potentially misvalued.'),
  ('97007', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized the direct PE inputs for CPT code 97007 (mechanical scalp cooling, cap supply with head measurement, fitting, and patient education) as proposed, including 27 minutes of CA021 clinical labor time instead of the RUC-recommended 5 minutes; this is a PE-only code and no work RVU is finalized."}', 'After consideration of the public comments, we are finalizing the direct PE inputs for the scalp cooling services as proposed, with the addition of 30 minutes of equipment time for the medical recliner chair in CPT codes 97008 and 97009. We did not propose, and we are not finalizing a work RVU for the three codes in this family.'),
  ('97008', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized the direct PE inputs for CPT code 97008 (mechanical scalp cooling; hair preparation, cap placement, therapy initiation, pre-cooling) as proposed, with the addition of 30 minutes of equipment time for the medical recliner chair (EF009); this is a PE-only code and no work RVU is finalized."}', 'After consideration of the public comments, we are finalizing the direct PE inputs for the scalp cooling services as proposed, with the addition of 30 minutes of equipment time for the medical recliner chair in CPT codes 97008 and 97009. We did not propose, and we are not finalizing a work RVU for the three codes in this family.'),
  ('97009', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized the direct PE inputs for CPT code 97009 (mechanical scalp cooling; each 30 minutes) as proposed, with the addition of 30 minutes of equipment time for the medical recliner chair (EF009); this is a PE-only code and no work RVU is finalized."}', 'After consideration of the public comments, we are finalizing the direct PE inputs for the scalp cooling services as proposed, with the addition of 30 minutes of equipment time for the medical recliner chair in CPT codes 97008 and 97009. We did not propose, and we are not finalizing a work RVU for the three codes in this family.'),
  ('97124', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that the new manual therapy hand instruments equipment item (EQ416, priced at $1,795 with a 15-year useful life) is NOT added to the direct practice expense equipment inputs for CPT 97124 (massage therapy), because CMS has no data showing that use of these instruments is typical for the service; the valuation of 97124 therefore does not include this equipment."}', 'therapy hand instruments is typical in CPT codes 97140 and 97124, we'),
  ('97140', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that the new manual therapy hand instruments equipment item (EQ416, priced at $1,795 with a 15-year useful life) is NOT added to the direct practice expense equipment inputs for CPT 97140 (manual therapy), because CMS has no data showing that use of these instruments is typical for the service; the valuation of 97140 therefore does not include this equipment."}', 'are not adding them to the equipment inputs for these two codes.'),
  ('97550', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 97550 (caregiver training services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '97550, 97551, and 97552 (codes for caregiver training'),
  ('97551', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 97551 (caregiver training services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '97550, 97551, and 97552 (codes for caregiver training'),
  ('97552', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 97552 (caregiver training services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '97550, 97551, and 97552 (codes for caregiver training'),
  ('98000', 'telehealth_allowed', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 98000, one of the telemedicine E/M services (CPT codes 98000 through 98015), is NOT added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List for CY 2026. These codes are assigned status indicator I (not valid for Medicare purposes), are not separately payable under the PFS, and so fail step 1 of the telehealth review process."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to not add the telemedicine E/M services (CPT codes 98000 through 98015) to the Medicare Telehealth Services List.'),
  ('98001', 'telehealth_allowed', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 98001, one of the telemedicine E/M services (CPT codes 98000 through 98015), is NOT added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List for CY 2026. These codes are assigned status indicator I (not valid for Medicare purposes), are not separately payable under the PFS, and so fail step 1 of the telehealth review process."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to not add the telemedicine E/M services (CPT codes 98000 through 98015) to the Medicare Telehealth Services List.'),
