  ('98016', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: beginning January 1, 2026, RHCs and FQHCs furnishing brief virtual check-in services must report CPT code 98016 (in place of unbundled HCPCS G0071) to receive separate payment, paid at the national non-facility PFS payment rate when the code is on an RHC or FQHC claim."}', 'code 98016 to receive separate payment'),
  ('98975', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized valuation for CPT code 98975 (RTM initial set-up and patient education) as proposed, except revising the clinical staff type to PTA (L039B) from RN/LPN/MTA; the RUC-recommended remote monitoring program enrollment fee was not included as a direct PE input."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed, with the exception of revising the clinical staff type to PTA from RN/LPN/MTA.'),
  ('98975', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CPT code 98975, CMS is adopting all descriptors, guidelines, prefatory language, and parenthetical changes in the Remote Monitoring section of the 2026 CPT codebook, including the revised reporting requirement of 2 days of monitoring in a 30-day period (as opposed to 16 days)."}', 'furnishes this service, and the PTA (L039B) blend is the typical clinical labor type. We will be adopting all descriptors, guidelines, prefatory language, and parenthetical changes made to the Remote Monitoring section of the 2026 edition of the CPT codebook, including'),
  ('98976', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized actively pricing CPT code 98976 for CY 2026 by crosswalking its PE RVU to CPT code 99454, rather than contractor pricing as proposed; both 98976 and 98984 receive the same valuation."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing actively pricing CPT codes 98976 and 98984 by crosswalking the PE RVU to CPT code 99454.'),
  ('98976', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"RTM device supply CPT code 98976 (respiratory, 16-30 days of data transmission per 30-day period) is not additive with the new 2-15 day RTM codes; practitioners may bill only one of these codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days."}', 'The 2 to 15 day codes (99445, 98984, 98985, and 98986) and 16 to 30 day codes (99454, 98976, 98977, 98978) are not additive and are not a base and add-on code structure. Billing practitioners would only bill for one of those codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days.'),
  ('98977', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the PE RVU for CPT code 98977 (RTM device supply/data transmission) by dividing the CY 2026 OPPS Geometric Mean Cost for CPT code 98977 by the CY 2026 non-qualifying APM PFS conversion factor; CPT codes 98985 and 98977 receive the same finalized PE RVU since the device is supplied for the full 30-day period."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing calculating this value by dividing the CY 2026 OPPS Geometric Mean Cost (GMC) for CPT code 98977, which is represented [[Page 49404]] in a dollar amount, by the CY 2026 non-qualifying APM PFS conversion factor (CF), which represents the dollar value of an RVU, to convert the GMC dollar amount into RVUs. The resulting value will be our finalized PE RVU for CPT codes 98985 and 98977.'),
  ('98977', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"RTM device supply CPT code 98977 (musculoskeletal, 16-30 days of data transmission per 30-day period) is not additive with the new 2-15 day RTM codes; practitioners may bill only one of these codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days."}', 'The 2 to 15 day codes (99445, 98984, 98985, and 98986) and 16 to 30 day codes (99454, 98976, 98977, 98978) are not additive and are not a base and add-on code structure. Billing practitioners would only bill for one of those codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days.'),
  ('98978', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized as proposed maintaining contractor pricing for PE-only CPT code 98978 for CY 2026, citing evolving technologies and significant pricing variability; Medicare Administrative Contractors will determine payment."}', 'CPT codes 98986 and 98978 are PE-only codes. We proposed to contractor price CPT code 98986 and proposed to maintain contractor pricing for CPT code 98978.'),
  ('98978', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"RTM device supply CPT code 98978 (cognitive behavioral therapy, 16-30 days of data transmission per 30-day period) is not additive with the new 2-15 day RTM codes; practitioners may bill only one of these codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days."}', 'The 2 to 15 day codes (99445, 98984, 98985, and 98986) and 16 to 30 day codes (99454, 98976, 98977, 98978) are not additive and are not a base and add-on code structure. Billing practitioners would only bill for one of those codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days.'),
  ('98979', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized as proposed a work RVU of 0.31 for CPT code 98979 (remote therapeutic monitoring treatment management, 10 minutes), rejecting the RUC recommendation of 0.66, based on the total time ratio to CPT code 98980, with RN/LPN/MTA (L037D) clinical labor."}', 'For CPT code 98979, we disagreed with the RUC''s recommendation of 0.66 work RVUs and proposed a work RVU of 0.31, with 10 minutes or intraservice/total time. We proposed this work RVU for CPT code 98979'),
  ('98979', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is adopting the CPT requirement that CPT code 98979 (RTM treatment management, first 10 minutes) requires a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver; the interactive communication contributes to total time but need not represent the entire cumulative reported time. Time may not be counted more than once toward any service."}', 'The CPT code book states that CPT Codes 98979, 98980, 98981, 99470, 99457, and 99458 ``require a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver. The interactive communication contributes to the total time, but it does not need to represent the entire cumulative reported time of the treatment management service.'''''),
  ('98979', 'modifier_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"New RTM CPT code 98979 is designated a sometimes therapy code: it always requires a POC therapy modifier (GP or GO) when furnished by a PT, OT, or SLP, and the CQ/CO modifier policy for services of PTAs and OTAs applies to 98979 when the de minimis/10 percent standard is met."}', 'For the RTM codes designated as sometimes therapy, we are clarifying our policy about the appropriate use of the CQ/CO modifiers for services of PTAs and OTAs apply to the new RTM code 98979.'),
  ('98979', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 98979 (RTM treatment management, first 10 minutes) is not additive with CPT code 98980 (first 20 minutes); billing practitioners must choose the single most appropriate code for the time spent in that calendar month."}', 'In addition, the treatment management services describing the first 10 minutes (99470 and 98979) and first 20 minutes (99457 and 98980) of service are also not additive. Billing practitioners would choose the most appropriate code for the time spent that calendar month.'),
  ('98980', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized as proposed maintaining the current work RVU of 0.62 for CPT code 98980 (RTM treatment management, first 20 minutes), with the current 20 minutes of intraservice/total work time and current direct PE inputs, rejecting the RUC recommendation of 0.78, to maintain relativity between RPM and RTM codes."}', 'For CPT code 98980, we disagreed with the RUC''s recommendation of 0.78 work RVUs and are proposing to maintain the current work RVU of 0.62, the current 20 minutes of intraservice/total work time, and the current direct PE inputs. For CPT code 98981, we disagreed with the RUC''s recommendation of 0.70 work RVUs and proposed to maintain the current work RVU of 0.61 and the current direct PE inputs; the RUC recommended, and we are proposing to maintain the current 20 minutes of intraservice/total work time. These proposals were due to wanting to'),
  ('98980', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is adopting the CPT requirement that CPT code 98980 (RTM treatment management, first 20 minutes) requires a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver; the interactive communication contributes to total time but need not represent the entire cumulative reported time."}', 'The CPT code book states that CPT Codes 98979, 98980, 98981, 99470, 99457, and 99458 ``require a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver. The interactive communication contributes to the total time, but it does not need to represent the entire cumulative reported time of the treatment management service.'''''),
  ('98980', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 98980 (RTM treatment management, first 20 minutes) is not additive with the new first-10-minutes code 98979; billing practitioners must choose the single most appropriate code for the time spent in that calendar month."}', 'In addition, the treatment management services describing the first 10 minutes (99470 and 98979) and first 20 minutes (99457 and 98980) of service are also not additive. Billing practitioners would choose the most appropriate code for the time spent that calendar month.'),
  ('98981', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Add-on CPT code 98981 (RTM treatment management, each additional 20 minutes) may be billed when more than 20 minutes of treatment management is needed after CPT code 98980 is billed in the calendar month."}', 'In instances where more than 20 minutes of treatment management is needed after either 99457 or 98980 is billed, 99458 or 98981 can be used.'),
  ('98981', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized as proposed maintaining the current work RVU of 0.61 for CPT code 98981 (RTM treatment management, each additional 20 minutes), with the current direct PE inputs and 20 minutes of intraservice/total work time, rejecting the RUC recommendation of 0.70."}', 'For CPT code 98980, we disagreed with the RUC''s recommendation of 0.78 work RVUs and are proposing to maintain the current work RVU of 0.62, the current 20 minutes of intraservice/total work time, and the current direct PE inputs. For CPT code 98981, we disagreed with the RUC''s recommendation of 0.70 work RVUs and proposed to maintain the current work RVU of 0.61 and the current direct PE inputs; the RUC recommended, and we are proposing to maintain the current 20 minutes of intraservice/total work time. These proposals were due to wanting to'),
  ('98981', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is adopting the CPT requirement that CPT code 98981 (RTM treatment management, each additional 20 minutes) requires a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver; the interactive communication contributes to total time but need not represent the entire cumulative reported time."}', 'The CPT code book states that CPT Codes 98979, 98980, 98981, 99470, 99457, and 99458 ``require a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver. The interactive communication contributes to the total time, but it does not need to represent the entire cumulative reported time of the treatment management service.'''''),
  ('98984', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized actively pricing CPT code 98984 for CY 2026 by crosswalking its PE RVU to CPT code 99454, rather than contractor pricing as proposed; both 98976 and 98984 receive the same valuation."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing actively pricing CPT codes 98976 and 98984 by crosswalking the PE RVU to CPT code 99454.'),
  ('98984', 'modifier_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"New RTM device supply CPT code 98984 is designated a sometimes therapy code (requiring a POC therapy modifier when furnished under a therapy plan of care), but the CQ/CO modifiers for PTA/OTA services are not applicable to it because it is based on existing device code 98976."}', 'However, the CQ/CO are not applicable to the RTM device codes 98984 and 98985 as they are based on the exiting codes 98976 and 98977.'),
  ('98984', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"New RTM device supply CPT code 98984 (2-15 days of data transmission per 30-day period) is not additive with the corresponding 16-30 day code; practitioners may bill only one of these codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days."}', 'The 2 to 15 day codes (99445, 98984, 98985, and 98986) and 16 to 30 day codes (99454, 98976, 98977, 98978) are not additive and are not a base and add-on code structure. Billing practitioners would only bill for one of those codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days.'),
  ('98985', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the PE RVU for CPT code 98985 (RTM device supply/data transmission) by dividing the CY 2026 OPPS Geometric Mean Cost for CPT code 98977 by the CY 2026 non-qualifying APM PFS conversion factor; CPT codes 98985 and 98977 receive the same finalized PE RVU since the device is supplied for the full 30-day period."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing calculating this value by dividing the CY 2026 OPPS Geometric Mean Cost (GMC) for CPT code 98977, which is represented [[Page 49404]] in a dollar amount, by the CY 2026 non-qualifying APM PFS conversion factor (CF), which represents the dollar value of an RVU, to convert the GMC dollar amount into RVUs. The resulting value will be our finalized PE RVU for CPT codes 98985 and 98977.'),
  ('98985', 'modifier_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"New RTM device supply CPT code 98985 is designated a sometimes therapy code (requiring a POC therapy modifier when furnished under a therapy plan of care), but the CQ/CO modifiers for PTA/OTA services are not applicable to it because it is based on existing device code 98977."}', 'However, the CQ/CO are not applicable to the RTM device codes 98984 and 98985 as they are based on the exiting codes 98976 and 98977.'),
  ('98985', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"New RTM device supply CPT code 98985 (2-15 days of data transmission per 30-day period) is not additive with the corresponding 16-30 day code; practitioners may bill only one of these codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days."}', 'The 2 to 15 day codes (99445, 98984, 98985, and 98986) and 16 to 30 day codes (99454, 98976, 98977, 98978) are not additive and are not a base and add-on code structure. Billing practitioners would only bill for one of those codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days.'),
  ('98986', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized as proposed contractor pricing for PE-only CPT code 98986 for CY 2026, citing evolving technologies and significant pricing variability; Medicare Administrative Contractors will determine payment."}', 'CPT codes 98986 and 98978 are PE-only codes. We proposed to contractor price CPT code 98986 and proposed to maintain contractor pricing for CPT code 98978.'),
  ('98986', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"New RTM device supply CPT code 98986 (2-15 days of data transmission per 30-day period) is not additive with the corresponding 16-30 day code; practitioners may bill only one of these codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days."}', 'The 2 to 15 day codes (99445, 98984, 98985, and 98986) and 16 to 30 day codes (99454, 98976, 98977, 98978) are not additive and are not a base and add-on code structure. Billing practitioners would only bill for one of those codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days.'),
  ('99024', 'documentation_required', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99024 is the no-pay code that practitioners in nine states and in practices of 10 or more National Provider Identifiers (NPIs) are required to use to report post-operative visits falling within global surgical periods, under the MACRA-mandated claims-based reporting system."}', 'required practitioners in nine states and in practices of 10 or more National Provider Identifiers (NPIs) to report post-operative visits falling with global periods using no-pay HCPCS code 99024.'),
  ('99091', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized maintaining the current work RVU of 1.10 and corresponding physician time inputs for CPT code 99091 (collection and interpretation of physiologic data), rejecting the RUC recommendation of 0.70; RPM codes will be resurveyed after 1 year of utilization data under the 2026 code structure."}', 'For CPT code 99091, we disagree with the RUC''s recommendation of 0.70 work RVUs and proposed to maintain the current work RVU of 1.10 and the corresponding physician time inputs.'),
  ('99201', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99201 is included in the finalized range 99201 through 99215 (office or other outpatient E/M visits) designated as primary care service codes for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99201 through 99215 (codes for office or other outpatient visit'),
  ('99211', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"For services furnished after December 31, 2025, the direct supervision requirement for CPT 99211 (established patient office/outpatient visit that may not require physician presence) may be met by the supervising physician''s or practitioner''s virtual presence through audio/video real-time communications technology (excluding audio-only), per the revision of 42 CFR 410.26(a)(2) finalized in the CY 2025 PFS final rule."}', 'direct supervision shall continue to include virtual presence through audio/video real-time communications technology (excluding audio-only): services provided ``incident to'''' a physician''s service when they are provided by auxiliary personnel employed by the physician and working under his or her direct supervision and for which the underlying HCPCS code has been assigned a PC/TC indicator of ''5''; and services described by CPT code 99211 (office and other outpatient visit for the evaluation and management of an established patient that may not require the presence of a physician or other qualified health care professional).'),
  ('99215', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99215 is included in the finalized range 99201 through 99215 (office or other outpatient E/M visits) designated as primary care service codes for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99201 through 99215 (codes for office or other outpatient visit'),
  ('99231', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"The frequency limitation of one subsequent hospital inpatient/observation telehealth visit every 3 days is permanently removed for CPT 99231 beginning CY 2026; CMS finalized the removal as proposed, deferring to practitioner professional judgment."}', 'We proposed to permanently remove frequency limitations on furnishing these services via telehealth for the following codes relating to Subsequent Inpatient Visits, Subsequent Nursing Facility Visits, and Critical Care Consultation Services:'),
  ('99232', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"The frequency limitation of one subsequent hospital inpatient/observation telehealth visit every 3 days is permanently removed for CPT 99232 beginning CY 2026; CMS finalized the removal as proposed."}', 'We proposed to permanently remove frequency limitations on furnishing these services via telehealth for the following codes relating to Subsequent Inpatient Visits, Subsequent Nursing Facility Visits, and Critical Care Consultation Services:'),
  ('99233', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"The frequency limitation of one subsequent hospital inpatient/observation telehealth visit every 3 days is permanently removed for CPT 99233 beginning CY 2026; CMS finalized the removal as proposed."}', 'We proposed to permanently remove frequency limitations on furnishing these services via telehealth for the following codes relating to Subsequent Inpatient Visits, Subsequent Nursing Facility Visits, and Critical Care Consultation Services:'),
  ('99304', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99304 is included in the finalized range 99304 through 99318 (nursing facility professional services) designated as primary care service codes for MSSP beneficiary assignment for performance years starting January 1, 2026 and later; services on an FQHC or RHC claim furnished in a skilled nursing facility are excluded (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99304 through 99318 (codes for professional services furnished'),
  ('99307', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"The frequency limitation of one subsequent nursing facility telehealth visit every 14 days is permanently removed for CPT 99307 beginning CY 2026; CMS finalized the removal as proposed."}', 'We proposed to permanently remove frequency limitations on furnishing these services via telehealth for the following codes relating to Subsequent Inpatient Visits, Subsequent Nursing Facility Visits, and Critical Care Consultation Services:'),
  ('99308', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"The frequency limitation of one subsequent nursing facility telehealth visit every 14 days is permanently removed for CPT 99308 beginning CY 2026; CMS finalized the removal as proposed."}', 'We proposed to permanently remove frequency limitations on furnishing these services via telehealth for the following codes relating to Subsequent Inpatient Visits, Subsequent Nursing Facility Visits, and Critical Care Consultation Services:'),
  ('99309', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"The frequency limitation of one subsequent nursing facility telehealth visit every 14 days is permanently removed for CPT 99309 beginning CY 2026; CMS finalized the removal as proposed."}', 'We proposed to permanently remove frequency limitations on furnishing these services via telehealth for the following codes relating to Subsequent Inpatient Visits, Subsequent Nursing Facility Visits, and Critical Care Consultation Services:'),
  ('99310', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"The frequency limitation of one subsequent nursing facility telehealth visit every 14 days is permanently removed for CPT 99310 beginning CY 2026; CMS finalized the removal as proposed."}', 'We proposed to permanently remove frequency limitations on furnishing these services via telehealth for the following codes relating to Subsequent Inpatient Visits, Subsequent Nursing Facility Visits, and Critical Care Consultation Services:'),
  ('99318', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99318 is included in the finalized range 99304 through 99318 (nursing facility professional services) designated as primary care service codes for MSSP beneficiary assignment for performance years starting January 1, 2026 and later; services on an FQHC or RHC claim furnished in a skilled nursing facility are excluded (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99304 through 99318 (codes for professional services furnished'),
  ('99319', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99319 is included in the finalized range 99319 through 99340 (patient domiciliary, rest home, or custodial care visits) designated as primary care service codes for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99319 through 99340 (codes for patient domiciliary, rest home,'),
  ('99340', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99340 is included in the finalized range 99319 through 99340 (patient domiciliary, rest home, or custodial care visits) designated as primary care service codes for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99319 through 99340 (codes for patient domiciliary, rest home,'),
  ('99341', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99341 (home or residence E/M visit) is finalized as a base code for the visit complexity add-on HCPCS code G2211 beginning CY 2026, so G2211 may be billed as an add-on with this code."}', 'After reviewing all the comments, we are finalizing as proposed, to allow HCPCS code G2211 to be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visits code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350). We are also finalizing refinement of the'),
  ('99341', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99341 is included in the finalized range 99341 through 99350 (E/M services furnished in a patient''s home) designated as primary care service codes for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99341 through 99350 (codes for evaluation and management'),
  ('99342', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99342 (home or residence E/M visit) is finalized as a base code for the visit complexity add-on HCPCS code G2211 beginning CY 2026, so G2211 may be billed as an add-on with this code."}', 'After reviewing all the comments, we are finalizing as proposed, to allow HCPCS code G2211 to be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visits code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350). We are also finalizing refinement of the'),
  ('99344', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99344 (home or residence E/M visit) is finalized as a base code for the visit complexity add-on HCPCS code G2211 beginning CY 2026, so G2211 may be billed as an add-on with this code."}', 'After reviewing all the comments, we are finalizing as proposed, to allow HCPCS code G2211 to be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visits code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350). We are also finalizing refinement of the'),
  ('99345', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99345 (home or residence E/M visit) is finalized as a base code for the visit complexity add-on HCPCS code G2211 beginning CY 2026, so G2211 may be billed as an add-on with this code."}', 'After reviewing all the comments, we are finalizing as proposed, to allow HCPCS code G2211 to be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visits code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350). We are also finalizing refinement of the'),
  ('99347', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99347 (home or residence E/M visit) is finalized as a base code for the visit complexity add-on HCPCS code G2211 beginning CY 2026, so G2211 may be billed as an add-on with this code."}', 'After reviewing all the comments, we are finalizing as proposed, to allow HCPCS code G2211 to be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visits code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350). We are also finalizing refinement of the'),
  ('99348', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99348 (home or residence E/M visit) is finalized as a base code for the visit complexity add-on HCPCS code G2211 beginning CY 2026, so G2211 may be billed as an add-on with this code."}', 'After reviewing all the comments, we are finalizing as proposed, to allow HCPCS code G2211 to be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visits code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350). We are also finalizing refinement of the'),
  ('99349', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99349 (home or residence E/M visit) is finalized as a base code for the visit complexity add-on HCPCS code G2211 beginning CY 2026, so G2211 may be billed as an add-on with this code."}', 'After reviewing all the comments, we are finalizing as proposed, to allow HCPCS code G2211 to be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visits code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350). We are also finalizing refinement of the'),
  ('99350', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99350 (home or residence E/M visit) is finalized as a base code for the visit complexity add-on HCPCS code G2211 beginning CY 2026, so G2211 may be billed as an add-on with this code."}', 'After reviewing all the comments, we are finalizing as proposed, to allow HCPCS code G2211 to be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visits code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350). We are also finalizing refinement of the'),
  ('99350', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99350 is included in the finalized range 99341 through 99350 (E/M services furnished in a patient''s home) designated as primary care service codes for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99341 through 99350 (codes for evaluation and management'),
  ('99354', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99354, an add-on code for prolonged E/M or psychotherapy services beyond the typical time of the primary procedure, counts as a primary care service for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for performance years starting January 1, 2026, only when the base code is also a primary care service code under 42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x)."}', '99354 and 99355 (add-on codes, for prolonged evaluation and'),
  ('99354', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99354 (prolonged services) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for purposes of beneficiary assignment, as reaffirmed in the CY 2026 PFS final rule."}', 'The new HCPCS codes are also similar to CPT codes 99354 and 99355 (83 FR 59965 through 59968), which likewise are included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment.'),
  ('99355', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99355, an add-on code for prolonged E/M or psychotherapy services beyond the typical time of the primary procedure, counts as a primary care service for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for performance years starting January 1, 2026, only when the base code is also a primary care service code under 42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x)."}', '99354 and 99355 (add-on codes, for prolonged evaluation and'),
  ('99355', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99355 (prolonged services) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for purposes of beneficiary assignment, as reaffirmed in the CY 2026 PFS final rule."}', 'The new HCPCS codes are also similar to CPT codes 99354 and 99355 (83 FR 59965 through 59968), which likewise are included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment.'),
  ('99406', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99406 (smoking and tobacco-use cessation counseling) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99406 and 99407 (codes for smoking and tobacco-use cessation'),
  ('99407', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99407 (smoking and tobacco-use cessation counseling) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99406 and 99407 (codes for smoking and tobacco-use cessation'),
  ('99421', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99421 (online digital evaluation and management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99421, 99422, and 99423 (codes for online digital evaluation'),
  ('99422', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99422 (online digital evaluation and management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99421, 99422, and 99423 (codes for online digital evaluation'),
  ('99423', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99423 (online digital evaluation and management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99421, 99422, and 99423 (codes for online digital evaluation'),
  ('99424', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99424 (principal care management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99424, 99425, 99426, and 99427 (codes for principal care'),
  ('99425', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99425 (principal care management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99424, 99425, 99426, and 99427 (codes for principal care'),
  ('99426', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99426 (principal care management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99424, 99425, 99426, and 99427 (codes for principal care'),
  ('99427', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99427 (principal care management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99424, 99425, 99426, and 99427 (codes for principal care'),
  ('99437', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99437 (chronic care management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99437, 99487, 99489, 99490 and 99491 (codes for chronic care'),
  ('99439', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99439 (non-complex chronic care management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99439 (code for non-complex chronic care management).'),
  ('99445', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized setting the PE RVU for new CPT code 99445 (RPM device supply, 2-15 days) by dividing the CY 2026 OPPS Geometric Mean Cost for CPT code 99454 by the CY 2026 non-qualifying APM PFS conversion factor; 99445 and 99454 receive the same valuation because the device is supplied for the full 30-day period."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing calculating this value by dividing the CY 2026 OPPS Geometric Mean Cost (GMC) for CPT code 99454, which is represented in a dollar amount, by the CY 2026 non-qualifying APM PFS conversion factor (CF), which represents the dollar value of an RVU, to convert the GMC dollar amount into RVUs. The resulting value will be our finalized PE RVU for CPT codes 99445 and 99454.'),
  ('99445', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99445 (RPM device supply, 2-15 days of data transmission per 30-day period) is not additive with the 16-30 day code 99454; practitioners may bill only one of these codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days."}', 'The 2 to 15 day codes (99445, 98984, 98985, and 98986) and 16 to 30 day codes (99454, 98976, 98977, 98978) are not additive and are not a base and add-on code structure. Billing practitioners would only bill for one of those codes for the appropriate number of days of data transmission per 30 days.'),
  ('99452', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99452 (interprofessional consultation service) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99452 (code for interprofessional consultation service).'),
  ('99453', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended PE inputs for PE-only CPT code 99453 (RPM initial setup and patient education) and is adopting the 2026 CPT codebook parenthetical changes for this code, under which 99453 now requires 2 days of monitoring in a 30-day period for reporting instead of 16."}', 'We will be adopting all descriptors, guidelines, prefatory language, and parenthetical changes made to the Remote Monitoring section of the 2026 edition of the CPT codebook, including for CPT code 99453.'),
  ('99454', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized setting the PE RVU for CPT code 99454 (RPM device supply, 16-30 days) by dividing the CY 2026 OPPS Geometric Mean Cost for CPT code 99454 by the CY 2026 non-qualifying APM PFS conversion factor, using OPPS cost data instead of RUC-recommended direct PE inputs; 99445 and 99454 receive the same valuation."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing calculating this value by dividing the CY 2026 OPPS Geometric Mean Cost (GMC) for CPT code 99454, which is represented in a dollar amount, by the CY 2026 non-qualifying APM PFS conversion factor (CF), which represents the dollar value of an RVU, to convert the GMC dollar amount into RVUs. The resulting value will be our finalized PE RVU for CPT codes 99445 and 99454.'),
  ('99457', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized maintaining the current work RVU of 0.61, current work time of 20 minutes, and current direct PE inputs for CPT code 99457 (RPM treatment management, first 20 minutes), rejecting the RUC recommendation of 0.45."}', 'For CPT code 99457, we disagreed with the RUC''s recommendation of 0.45 work RVUs and proposed to maintain the current work RVU of 0.61, the current work time of 20 minutes, and the current direct PE inputs.'),
  ('99457', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is adopting the CPT requirement that CPT code 99457 (RPM treatment management, first 20 minutes) requires a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver; the interactive communication contributes to total time but need not represent the entire cumulative reported time."}', 'The CPT code book states that CPT Codes 98979, 98980, 98981, 99470, 99457, and 99458 ``require a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver. The interactive communication contributes to the total time, but it does not need to represent the entire cumulative reported time of the treatment management service.'''''),
  ('99457', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99457 (RPM treatment management, first 20 minutes) is not additive with the new first-10-minutes code 99470; billing practitioners must choose the single most appropriate code for the time spent in that calendar month."}', 'In addition, the treatment management services describing the first 10 minutes (99470 and 98979) and first 20 minutes (99457 and 98980) of service are also not additive. Billing practitioners would choose the most appropriate code for the time spent that calendar month.'),
  ('99458', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Add-on CPT code 99458 (RPM treatment management, each additional 20 minutes) may be billed when more than 20 minutes of treatment management is needed after CPT code 99457 is billed in the calendar month."}', 'In instances where more than 20 minutes of treatment management is needed after either 99457 or 98980 is billed, 99458 or 98981 can be used.'),
  ('99458', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.61 for CPT code 99458 (RPM treatment management, each additional 20 minutes) while maintaining the current direct PE inputs rather than the RUC-recommended PE inputs."}', 'We proposed the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.61 for CPT code 99458, as this work RVU was reviewed by the RUC and resulted in no recommended changes for CY 2026.'),
  ('99458', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is adopting the CPT requirement that CPT code 99458 (RPM treatment management, each additional 20 minutes) requires a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver; the interactive communication contributes to total time but need not represent the entire cumulative reported time."}', 'The CPT code book states that CPT Codes 98979, 98980, 98981, 99470, 99457, and 99458 ``require a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver. The interactive communication contributes to the total time, but it does not need to represent the entire cumulative reported time of the treatment management service.'''''),
  ('99470', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized a work RVU of 0.31 with 10 minutes of intraservice/total time for new CPT code 99470 (RPM treatment management, first 10 minutes), rejecting the RUC recommendation of 0.39, based on a 50 percent total-time ratio to CPT code 99457; 5 minutes CA021 and 15 minutes CA037 clinical labor time were also finalized."}', 'For CPT code 99470, we disagreed with the RUC''s recommendation of 0.39 work RVUs and proposed a work RVU of 0.31, with 10 minutes or intraservice/total time.'),
  ('99470', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is adopting the CPT requirement that CPT code 99470 (RPM treatment management, first 10 minutes) requires a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver; the interactive communication contributes to total time but need not represent the entire cumulative reported time."}', 'The CPT code book states that CPT Codes 98979, 98980, 98981, 99470, 99457, and 99458 ``require a live, interactive communication with the patient/caregiver. The interactive communication contributes to the total time, but it does not need to represent the entire cumulative reported time of the treatment management service.'''''),
  ('99470', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT code 99470 (RPM treatment management, first 10 minutes) is not additive with CPT code 99457 (first 20 minutes); billing practitioners must choose the single most appropriate code for the time spent in that calendar month."}', 'In addition, the treatment management services describing the first 10 minutes (99470 and 98979) and first 20 minutes (99457 and 98980) of service are also not additive. Billing practitioners would choose the most appropriate code for the time spent that calendar month.'),
  ('99473', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended direct PE inputs without refinement for PE-only CPT code 99473 (self-measured blood pressure monitoring, device setup and patient education), as the RUC review resulted in no recommended changes."}', 'For CPT code 99473, which is a PE-only code, we proposed the RUC- recommended direct PE inputs without refinement, as this code was reviewed by the RUC and resulted in no recommended changes for CY 2026.'),
  ('99474', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.18 and direct PE inputs without refinement for CPT code 99474 (self-measured blood pressure monitoring), as the RUC review resulted in no recommended changes."}', 'For CPT code 99474, we proposed the RUC-recommended work RVU of 0.18 and direct PE inputs without refinement, as this code was reviewed by the RUC and resulted in no recommended changes for CY 2026.'),
  ('99483', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99483 (assessment of and care planning for patients with cognitive impairment) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99483 (code for assessment of and care planning for patients'),
  ('99484', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT/HCPCS code 99484 (general behavioral health integration (BHI) care management) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment, and that list (Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix)) is carried into the finalized definition at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) for performance years starting January 1, 2026."}', 'These new HCPCS codes are designed to allow for the payment of services that, when reported as standalone services, are currently included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment when furnished in conjunction with APCM services: BHI (CPT codes 99484, 99492, 99493 and 99494), CoCM (HCPCS code G2214), and APCM (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558)'),
  ('99484', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"The time-based requirements for CPT code 99484 remain in effect when the code is billed on a standalone basis outside of the provision of APCM services; only the parallel APCM add-on G-codes (G0568, G0569, G0570) remove the counting of minutes."}', 'are introduced, we continue to believe that removing the time-based requirements for HCPCS codes G0568, G0569, and G0570 when billed in conjunction with an APCM base code (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558) will ultimately reduce administrative burden, as it aligns the documentation requirements of the APCM codes with the add-on codes. The time-based requirements for CPT codes 99492, 99493, and 99484 remain in the instance these CPT codes are billed on a standalone basis, outside of the provision of APCM services.'),
  ('99487', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99487 (chronic care management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99437, 99487, 99489, 99490 and 99491 (codes for chronic care'),
  ('99489', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99489 (chronic care management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99437, 99487, 99489, 99490 and 99491 (codes for chronic care'),
  ('99490', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99490 (chronic care management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99437, 99487, 99489, 99490 and 99491 (codes for chronic care'),
  ('99491', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99491 (chronic care management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99437, 99487, 99489, 99490 and 99491 (codes for chronic care'),
  ('99492', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT/HCPCS code 99492 (initial-month psychiatric collaborative care management (CoCM)) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment, and that list (Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix)) is carried into the finalized definition at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) for performance years starting January 1, 2026."}', 'These new HCPCS codes are designed to allow for the payment of services that, when reported as standalone services, are currently included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment when furnished in conjunction with APCM services: BHI (CPT codes 99484, 99492, 99493 and 99494), CoCM (HCPCS code G2214), and APCM (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558)'),
  ('99492', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"The time-based requirements for CPT code 99492 remain in effect when the code is billed on a standalone basis outside of the provision of APCM services; only the parallel APCM add-on G-codes (G0568, G0569, G0570) remove the counting of minutes."}', 'are introduced, we continue to believe that removing the time-based requirements for HCPCS codes G0568, G0569, and G0570 when billed in conjunction with an APCM base code (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558) will ultimately reduce administrative burden, as it aligns the documentation requirements of the APCM codes with the add-on codes. The time-based requirements for CPT codes 99492, 99493, and 99484 remain in the instance these CPT codes are billed on a standalone basis, outside of the provision of APCM services.'),
  ('99493', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT/HCPCS code 99493 (subsequent-month psychiatric collaborative care management (CoCM)) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment, and that list (Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix)) is carried into the finalized definition at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) for performance years starting January 1, 2026."}', 'These new HCPCS codes are designed to allow for the payment of services that, when reported as standalone services, are currently included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment when furnished in conjunction with APCM services: BHI (CPT codes 99484, 99492, 99493 and 99494), CoCM (HCPCS code G2214), and APCM (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558)'),
  ('99493', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"The time-based requirements for CPT code 99493 remain in effect when the code is billed on a standalone basis outside of the provision of APCM services; only the parallel APCM add-on G-codes (G0568, G0569, G0570) remove the counting of minutes."}', 'are introduced, we continue to believe that removing the time-based requirements for HCPCS codes G0568, G0569, and G0570 when billed in conjunction with an APCM base code (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558) will ultimately reduce administrative burden, as it aligns the documentation requirements of the APCM codes with the add-on codes. The time-based requirements for CPT codes 99492, 99493, and 99484 remain in the instance these CPT codes are billed on a standalone basis, outside of the provision of APCM services.'),
  ('99494', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: beginning January 1, 2026, RHCs and FQHCs can bill CPT add-on code 99494 (psychiatric collaborative care management, each additional 30 minutes per calendar month) as part of the unbundling of HCPCS G0512, once the minimum time threshold is met, paid at the national non-facility PFS payment rate."}', 'FQHCs can bill CPT code 99494.'),
  ('99494', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT/HCPCS code 99494 (additional BHI/CoCM care management) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment, and that list (Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix)) is carried into the finalized definition at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) for performance years starting January 1, 2026."}', 'These new HCPCS codes are designed to allow for the payment of services that, when reported as standalone services, are currently included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment when furnished in conjunction with APCM services: BHI (CPT codes 99484, 99492, 99493 and 99494), CoCM (HCPCS code G2214), and APCM (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558)'),
  ('99495', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99495 (transitional care management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99495 and 99496 (codes for transitional care management'),
  ('99496', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99496 (transitional care management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99495 and 99496 (codes for transitional care management'),
  ('99497', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99497 (advance care planning) is finalized as a primary care service code for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for performance years starting January 1, 2026 and later; advance care planning services furnished in an inpatient setting are excluded (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99497 and 99498 (codes for advance care planning; services'),
  ('99498', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT 99498 (advance care planning) is finalized as a primary care service code for Medicare Shared Savings Program beneficiary assignment for performance years starting January 1, 2026 and later; advance care planning services furnished in an inpatient setting are excluded (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', '99497 and 99498 (codes for advance care planning; services'),
  ('A4100', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that non-sheet form skin substitutes (gels, powders, liquids, injectables) are eligible for separate payment as incident-to supplies and is revising HCPCS code A4100 (non-sheet form skin substitute, FDA cleared as a device, not otherwise specified, list in addition to primary procedure) to allow billing for non-sheet products lacking a more specific code; Medicare Administrative Contractors determine payment."}', 'we are also revising HCPCS code A4100 (Non-sheet form skin substitute, fda cleared as a device, not otherwise specified (list in addition to primary procedure) to allow billing for non-sheet form skin substitute products that do not yet have a more specific code.'),
  ('G0019', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized a revised code descriptor for Community Health Integration HCPCS code G0019 for CY 2026, replacing ''social determinants of health (SDOH)'' with ''upstream driver(s)'' and removing the term ''E/M'' from the initiating visit language; the service remains 60 minutes per calendar month performed by certified or trained auxiliary personnel under practitioner direction."}', 'descriptor for HCPCS code G0019 as follows:'),
  ('G0019', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that ''certified or trained auxiliary personnel'' for Community Health Integration HCPCS code G0019 also includes marriage and family therapists (MFTs) and mental health counselors (MHCs), in addition to clinical social workers. MFTs and MHCs can bill Medicare directly for CHI services they personally perform for the diagnosis or treatment of mental illness."}', 'codes: G0019, G0022, G0023, G0024, G0140, G0146, this also includes MFT'),
  ('G0022', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0022 (community health integration services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0019 and G0022 (codes for community health integration'),
  ('G0022', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that ''certified or trained auxiliary personnel'' for CHI add-on HCPCS code G0022 (each additional 30 minutes per calendar month) also includes marriage and family therapists (MFTs) and mental health counselors (MHCs). Like CSWs, MFTs and MHCs can bill Medicare directly for CHI services they personally perform for the diagnosis or treatment of mental illness."}', 'codes: G0019, G0022, G0023, G0024, G0140, G0146, this also includes MFT'),
  ('G0023', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0023 (principal illness navigation services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0023 and G0024 (codes for principal illness navigation'),
  ('G0023', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that ''certified or trained auxiliary personnel'' for Principal Illness Navigation HCPCS code G0023 (60 minutes per calendar month) also includes marriage and family therapists (MFTs) and mental health counselors (MHCs). MFTs and MHCs can bill Medicare directly for PIN services they personally perform for the diagnosis or treatment of mental illness."}', 'codes: G0019, G0022, G0023, G0024, G0140, G0146, this also includes MFT'),
  ('G0024', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0024 (principal illness navigation services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0023 and G0024 (codes for principal illness navigation'),
  ('G0024', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that ''certified or trained auxiliary personnel'' for PIN add-on HCPCS code G0024 (additional 30 minutes per calendar month) also includes marriage and family therapists (MFTs) and mental health counselors (MHCs). MFTs and MHCs can bill Medicare directly for PIN services they personally perform for the diagnosis or treatment of mental illness."}', 'codes: G0019, G0022, G0023, G0024, G0140, G0146, this also includes MFT'),
  ('G0071', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: beginning January 1, 2026, bundled HCPCS code G0071 (Virtual Communication Services) is unbundled for RHCs and FQHCs. RHCs and FQHCs furnishing communication technology-based and remote evaluation services must instead report the individual codes that make up G0071 (HCPCS G2010, G2250, and CPT 98016) to receive separate payment."}', 'HCPCS code G0071. That is, beginning January 1, 2026, RHCs and FQHCs'),
  ('G0071', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"In the CY 2026 PFS final rule, CMS finalized that RHCs and FQHCs are required to report the individual codes that make up the communications technology-based services (CTBS) HCPCS code G0071 rather than billing only the bundled code."}', 'We also finalized to require RHCs and FQHCs to report the individual codes that make up the communications technology- based services (CTBS), HCPCS code G0071 as well.'),
  ('G0101', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0101 (cervical or vaginal cancer screening) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0101 (code for cervical or vaginal cancer screening).'),
  ('G0108', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"DSMT services billed with G0108 require a referral from the physician, nurse practitioner (NP), physician assistant (PA), or certified nurse specialist (CNS) who is treating the patient for diabetes."}', 'DSMT services require a referral from the physician, nurse practitioner (NP), physician assistant (PA), or certified nurse specialist (CNS) who''s treating the patient for diabetes.'),
  ('G0108', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"The national average Medicare payment rate for G0108 (Diabetes Self-Management Training, individual, per 30 minutes) is $53.57."}', 'The Medicare procedure codes and national average payment rates for the DSMT claim are G0108--DSMT, individual, per 30 minutes ($53.57) and G0109--DSMT, group (2 or more), per 30 minutes ($15. 39).'),
  ('G0109', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"DSMT group services billed with G0109 require a referral from the physician, nurse practitioner (NP), physician assistant (PA), or certified nurse specialist (CNS) who is treating the patient for diabetes."}', 'DSMT services require a referral from the physician, nurse practitioner (NP), physician assistant (PA), or certified nurse specialist (CNS) who''s treating the patient for diabetes.'),
  ('G0109', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"The national average Medicare payment rate for G0109 (Diabetes Self-Management Training, group of 2 or more, per 30 minutes) is $15.39."}', 'The Medicare procedure codes and national average payment rates for the DSMT claim are G0108--DSMT, individual, per 30 minutes ($53.57) and G0109--DSMT, group (2 or more), per 30 minutes ($15. 39).'),
  ('G0136', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"All billing rules for HCPCS code G0136 remain the same: in addition to an outpatient E/M visit (other than a level 1 visit by clinical staff), G0136 can be furnished with CPT code 90791 (Psychiatric diagnostic evaluation) and the HBAI services described by CPT codes 96156, 96158, 96159, 96164, 96165, 96167, and 96168."}', 'furnished with CPT code 90791 (Psychiatric diagnostic evaluation) and'),
  ('G0136', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized retaining HCPCS code G0136 (not deleting it as proposed) and revising its descriptor for CY 2026 to ''Administration of a standardized, evidence-based assessment of physical activity and nutrition, 5-15 minutes, not more often than every 6 months.'' It is payable when both a physical activity and nutrition risk assessment are performed, or when only one is performed if only one is reasonable and necessary."}', 'we are finalizing retaining HCPCS code G0136 and revising the'),
  ('G0136', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"Under its revised descriptor finalized in the CY 2026 PFS final rule, HCPCS code G0136 (assessment of physical activity and nutrition, 5-15 minutes) may be billed not more often than every 6 months."}', 'we are instead revising the code descriptor to the following text: G0136--[Administration of a standardized, evidence- based assessment of physical activity and nutrition, 5-15 minutes, not more often than every 6 months]'),
  ('G0136', 'telehealth_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0136 will remain on the Medicare Telehealth Services List for CY 2026; CMS did not finalize its proposed removal of the code from the telehealth list."}', 'on the Medicare Telehealth Services List.'),
  ('G0136', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is retaining the current valuation for HCPCS code G0136, which is assigned a work RVU of 0.18, for CY 2026."}', 'We are also retaining the current valuation for HCPCS code G0136,'),
  ('G0138', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"For HCPCS G0138 (intravenous infusion of cipaglucosidase alfa-atga with oral miglustat administration), CMS finalized an increase in the price of the Opfolda 65 mg capsule supply input (SH111) from $33.00 to $33.52 per capsule, but declined to change the SH111 quantity in G0138 from 3.5 to 4 capsules, standing by the code''s previous valuation from the CY 2025 PFS final rule."}', 'valuation of G0138, where this same topic of the SH111 supply quantity'),
  ('G0140', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that ''certified or trained auxiliary personnel'' for HCPCS code G0140 (Principal Illness Navigation--Peer Support, 60 minutes per calendar month) also includes marriage and family therapists (MFTs) and mental health counselors (MHCs), in addition to clinical social workers."}', 'codes: G0019, G0022, G0023, G0024, G0140, G0146, this also includes MFT'),
  ('G0146', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that ''certified or trained auxiliary personnel'' for HCPCS code G0146 (Principal Illness Navigation--Peer Support, additional 30 minutes per calendar month) also includes marriage and family therapists (MFTs) and mental health counselors (MHCs), in addition to clinical social workers."}', 'codes: G0019, G0022, G0023, G0024, G0140, G0146, this also includes MFT'),
  ('G0248', 'telehealth_allowed', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0248 (home INR monitoring demonstration/training) is NOT added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List; CMS finalized as proposed because the service is furnished by clinical staff of a supplier and falls outside the section 1834(m) definition of a Medicare telehealth service (fails step 2 of the review process)."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to not add Home INR Monitoring (HCPCS code G0248) to the Medicare Telehealth Services List.'),
  ('G0317', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0317 (prolonged office or other outpatient E/M visit) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0317, G0318, and G2212 (codes for prolonged office or other'),
  ('G0318', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0318 (prolonged office or other outpatient E/M visit) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0317, G0318, and G2212 (codes for prolonged office or other'),
  ('G0402', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0402 (Welcome to Medicare visit) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0402 (code for the Welcome to Medicare visit).'),
  ('G0438', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0438 (annual wellness visit) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0438 and G0439 (codes for the annual wellness visits).'),
  ('G0439', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0439 (annual wellness visit) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0438 and G0439 (codes for the annual wellness visits).'),
  ('G0442', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0442 (alcohol misuse screening service) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0442 (code for alcohol misuse screening service).'),
  ('G0443', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0443 (alcohol misuse counseling service) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0443 (code for alcohol misuse counseling service).'),
  ('G0444', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0444 (annual depression screening service) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0444 (code for annual depression screening service).'),
  ('G0447', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"IBT for obesity (billed with G0447) must be furnished face-to-face on this schedule over a 12-month period: one visit every week for the first month; one visit every other week for months 2 to 6; and one visit every month for months 7 to 12, if the beneficiary meets the 3 kg weight loss requirement."}', 'IBT must be furnished face-to-face with the following session format over a 12-month period: one face-to- face visit every week for the first month; one face-to-face visit every other week for months 2 to 6; and one face-to-face visit every month for months 7 to 12, if the beneficiary meets the 3 kg weight loss requirement.'),
  ('G0447', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"Intensive Behavioral Therapy for obesity counseling billed with G0447 must be furnished by a qualified primary care physician or other primary care practitioner in a primary care setting."}', 'IBT counseling must be furnished by a qualified primary care physician or other primary care practitioner in a primary care setting.'),
  ('G0447', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"The national average Medicare reimbursement rate for G0447 (individual, face-to-face obesity counseling under Intensive Behavioral Therapy for Obesity, 15 minutes) is $31.70."}', 'The national average reimbursement rates for procedure codes required by Medicare for the IBT for Obesity claim are G0447 for individual, face-to-face obesity counseling, 15 minutes ($31.70) and G0473 for group counseling, 30 minutes ($11 to $13 across MACs).'),
  ('G0463', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0463 (services furnished in electing teaching amendment (ETA) hospitals) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0463 (code for services furnished in electing teaching'),
  ('G0465', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS declined to change the multiple procedure payment reduction status of HCPCS G0465 (blood-derived wound care): it retains a Multiple Procedure (MPPR) indicator of \"2\", under which payment is generally 100 percent of the highest valued procedure and 50 percent of the fee schedule amount for the remaining billed procedures."}', 'we continue to believe that HCPCS code G0465 has been appropriately assigned a Multiple Procedure indicator of ``2''''.'),
  ('G0473', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"IBT for obesity group counseling (billed with G0473) must be furnished face-to-face on this schedule over a 12-month period: one visit every week for the first month; one visit every other week for months 2 to 6; and one visit every month for months 7 to 12, if the beneficiary meets the 3 kg weight loss requirement."}', 'IBT must be furnished face-to-face with the following session format over a 12-month period: one face-to- face visit every week for the first month; one face-to-face visit every other week for months 2 to 6; and one face-to-face visit every month for months 7 to 12, if the beneficiary meets the 3 kg weight loss requirement.'),
  ('G0473', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"Intensive Behavioral Therapy for obesity group counseling billed with G0473 must be furnished by a qualified primary care physician or other primary care practitioner in a primary care setting."}', 'IBT counseling must be furnished by a qualified primary care physician or other primary care practitioner in a primary care setting.'),
  ('G0473', 'telehealth_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0473 (face-to-face behavioral counseling for obesity, group (2 to 10), 30 minutes) is added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List beginning in CY 2026, finalized as proposed."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to add Group Behavioral Counseling for Obesity (CPT code G0473) to the Medicare Telehealth Services List, beginning in CY 2026.'),
  ('G0473', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"The national average Medicare reimbursement rate for G0473 (group obesity counseling under Intensive Behavioral Therapy for Obesity, 30 minutes) ranges from $11 to $13 across Medicare Administrative Contractors (MACs)."}', 'The national average reimbursement rates for procedure codes required by Medicare for the IBT for Obesity claim are G0447 for individual, face-to-face obesity counseling, 15 minutes ($31.70) and G0473 for group counseling, 30 minutes ($11 to $13 across MACs).'),
  ('G0506', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0506 (chronic care management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0506 (code for chronic care management).'),
  ('G0508', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"The frequency limitation of one telehealth critical care consultation per day is permanently removed for HCPCS G0508 (telehealth consultation, critical care, initial) beginning CY 2026; CMS finalized the removal as proposed."}', 'We proposed to permanently remove frequency limitations on furnishing these services via telehealth for the following codes relating to Subsequent Inpatient Visits, Subsequent Nursing Facility Visits, and Critical Care Consultation Services:'),
  ('G0509', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"The frequency limitation of one telehealth critical care consultation per day is permanently removed for HCPCS G0509 (telehealth consultation, critical care, subsequent) beginning CY 2026; CMS finalized the removal as proposed."}', 'We proposed to permanently remove frequency limitations on furnishing these services via telehealth for the following codes relating to Subsequent Inpatient Visits, Subsequent Nursing Facility Visits, and Critical Care Consultation Services:'),
  ('G0512', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: beginning January 1, 2026, HCPCS code G0512 (RHC/FQHC psychiatric Collaborative Care Model, 70 min+) will no longer be payable when billed by RHCs and FQHCs. It is unbundled: RHCs and FQHCs must instead bill the individual CPT and HCPCS codes that make up G0512, paid at the national non-facility PFS payment rate when on an RHC or FQHC claim."}', 'HCPCS code G0512 will no longer be payable when billed by RHCs and'),
  ('G0512', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized a requirement that Rural Health Clinics (RHCs) and Federally Qualified Health Centers (FQHCs) report the individual codes that make up HCPCS code G0512, rather than reporting the bundled G0512 code, when billing psychiatric collaborative care model (CoCM) services."}', 'that make up HCPCS code G0512. We also finalized requiring RHCs and'),
  ('G0537', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0537 (cardiovascular risk assessment and risk management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0537 and G0538 (codes for cardiovascular risk assessment and'),
  ('G0538', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0538 (cardiovascular risk assessment and risk management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0537 and G0538 (codes for cardiovascular risk assessment and'),
  ('G0539', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0539 (individual behavior management/modification caregiver training services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0539 and G0540 (codes for individual behavior management/'),
  ('G0540', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0540 (individual behavior management/modification caregiver training services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0539 and G0540 (codes for individual behavior management/'),
  ('G0541', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0541 (direct care caregiver training services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0541, G0542, and G0543 (codes for direct care caregiver'),
  ('G0542', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0542 (direct care caregiver training services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0541, G0542, and G0543 (codes for direct care caregiver'),
  ('G0543', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0543 (direct care caregiver training services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0541, G0542, and G0543 (codes for direct care caregiver'),
  ('G0544', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0544 (post-discharge telephonic follow-up contacts intervention) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0544 (code for post-discharge telephonic follow-up contacts'),
  ('G0545', 'telehealth_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0545 (infectious disease add-on code for visit complexity inherent to hospital inpatient or observation care by an infectious diseases consultant) is added to the Medicare Telehealth Services List beginning in CY 2026, finalized as proposed."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed to add the Infections Disease Add-on (CPT code G0545) to the Medicare Telehealth Services List, beginning in CY 2026.'),
  ('G0552', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0552 (digital mental health treatment) is payable under the PFS only when the DMHT device is FDA-cleared under section 510(k) or granted De Novo authorization and classified at 21 CFR 882.5801, the billing practitioner incurs the device cost, and the device is furnished incident to the practitioner''s services in association with ongoing behavioral health treatment under a plan of care."}', 'cleared under section 510(k) of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act (FD&C Act) or granted De Novo authorization by FDA and in each instance classified at 21 CFR 882.5801. In addition, the billing practitioner must incur the cost of the DMHT device furnished to the beneficiary, and the furnishing of the DMHT device must be incident to the billing practitioner''s professional services in association with ongoing behavioral health treatment under a plan of care by the billing practitioner. Furthermore, we finalized that the billing practitioner must diagnose the patient with a mental health condition and prescribe'),
  ('G0552', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"For HCPCS code G0552, CMS clarified the patient must have a mental health condition diagnosis, but the billing practitioner does not need to be the practitioner who made the diagnosis. The billing practitioner must incur the cost of the DMHT device as a supply furnished incident to their professional services in association with ongoing behavioral health treatment under a plan of care."}', 'have a mental health condition diagnosis, but the billing practitioner'),
  ('G0552', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0552 (digital mental health treatment) may be billed by physicians and practitioners who are authorized to furnish services for the diagnosis and treatment of mental illness."}', 'Effective January 1, 2025, we finalized three HCPCS G-codes for DMHT devices, to be billed by physicians and practitioners who are authorized to furnish services for the diagnosis and treatment of mental illness: G0552 (Supply of digital mental health treatment device and initial education and onboarding, per course of treatment that augments a behavioral therapy plan); HCPCS code G0553 (First 20 minutes'),
  ('G0552', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS is not establishing a national payment rate for HCPCS code G0552 for CY 2026; pricing remains with the Medicare Administrative Contractors (MACs) because CMS lacks sufficient information to nationally price DMHT devices. CMS will work with MACs to improve understanding of G0552 billing rules and may consider national pricing in future rulemaking."}', 'sufficient information needed to establish national pricing for devices'),
  ('G0553', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0553 (digital mental health treatment) is payable under the PFS only when the DMHT device is FDA-cleared under section 510(k) or granted De Novo authorization and classified at 21 CFR 882.5801, the billing practitioner incurs the device cost, and the device is furnished incident to the practitioner''s services in association with ongoing behavioral health treatment under a plan of care."}', 'cleared under section 510(k) of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act (FD&C Act) or granted De Novo authorization by FDA and in each instance classified at 21 CFR 882.5801. In addition, the billing practitioner must incur the cost of the DMHT device furnished to the beneficiary, and the furnishing of the DMHT device must be incident to the billing practitioner''s professional services in association with ongoing behavioral health treatment under a plan of care by the billing practitioner. Furthermore, we finalized that the billing practitioner must diagnose the patient with a mental health condition and prescribe'),
  ('G0553', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"For HCPCS code G0553, the patient must have a mental health condition diagnosis, but CMS clarified that the billing practitioner does not need to be the practitioner who made the diagnosis; the billing practitioner must prescribe or order the DMHT device."}', 'or order the DMHT device. In the CY 2026 PFS proposed rule (90 FR 32352, 32503), we clarified that the patient must have a mental health condition diagnosis, but the billing practitioner does not need to be the practitioner who made the diagnosis. The patient could then use the DMHT device in settings according to how the device has been classified'),
  ('G0553', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0553 (digital mental health treatment) may be billed by physicians and practitioners who are authorized to furnish services for the diagnosis and treatment of mental illness."}', 'Effective January 1, 2025, we finalized three HCPCS G-codes for DMHT devices, to be billed by physicians and practitioners who are authorized to furnish services for the diagnosis and treatment of mental illness: G0552 (Supply of digital mental health treatment device and initial education and onboarding, per course of treatment that augments a behavioral therapy plan); HCPCS code G0553 (First 20 minutes'),
  ('G0554', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0554 (digital mental health treatment) is payable under the PFS only when the DMHT device is FDA-cleared under section 510(k) or granted De Novo authorization and classified at 21 CFR 882.5801, the billing practitioner incurs the device cost, and the device is furnished incident to the practitioner''s services in association with ongoing behavioral health treatment under a plan of care."}', 'cleared under section 510(k) of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act (FD&C Act) or granted De Novo authorization by FDA and in each instance classified at 21 CFR 882.5801. In addition, the billing practitioner must incur the cost of the DMHT device furnished to the beneficiary, and the furnishing of the DMHT device must be incident to the billing practitioner''s professional services in association with ongoing behavioral health treatment under a plan of care by the billing practitioner. Furthermore, we finalized that the billing practitioner must diagnose the patient with a mental health condition and prescribe'),
  ('G0554', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"For HCPCS code G0554, the patient must have a mental health condition diagnosis, but CMS clarified that the billing practitioner does not need to be the practitioner who made the diagnosis; the billing practitioner must prescribe or order the DMHT device."}', 'or order the DMHT device. In the CY 2026 PFS proposed rule (90 FR 32352, 32503), we clarified that the patient must have a mental health condition diagnosis, but the billing practitioner does not need to be the practitioner who made the diagnosis. The patient could then use the DMHT device in settings according to how the device has been classified'),
  ('G0554', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0554 (digital mental health treatment) may be billed by physicians and practitioners who are authorized to furnish services for the diagnosis and treatment of mental illness."}', 'Effective January 1, 2025, we finalized three HCPCS G-codes for DMHT devices, to be billed by physicians and practitioners who are authorized to furnish services for the diagnosis and treatment of mental illness: G0552 (Supply of digital mental health treatment device and initial education and onboarding, per course of treatment that augments a behavioral therapy plan); HCPCS code G0553 (First 20 minutes'),
  ('G0556', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0556 (Advanced Primary Care Management) is finalized as a base code for the new behavioral health integration add-on codes G0568, G0569, and G0570, which may be billed when G0556 is reported by the same practitioner in the same month."}', 'After consideration of the public comments, we are finalizing the establishment of three new G-codes to be billed as add-on services when the APCM base code (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558) is reported by the same practitioner in the same month: HCPCS code G0568, an add-on code based on CPT code 99492 for an initial month of CoCM services delivered to patients also receiving APCM services, HCPCS code G0569, an add-on code based on CPT code 99493 for CoCM services delivered to patients also receiving APCM services, and HCPCS code G0570, an add-on code for general behavioral health integration services based on CPT code 99484, and are'),
  ('G0556', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT/HCPCS code G0556 (Advanced Primary Care Management (APCM)) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment, and that list (Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix)) is carried into the finalized definition at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) for performance years starting January 1, 2026."}', 'These new HCPCS codes are designed to allow for the payment of services that, when reported as standalone services, are currently included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment when furnished in conjunction with APCM services: BHI (CPT codes 99484, 99492, 99493 and 99494), CoCM (HCPCS code G2214), and APCM (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558)'),
  ('G0557', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0557 (Advanced Primary Care Management) is finalized as a base code for the new behavioral health integration add-on codes G0568, G0569, and G0570, which may be billed when G0557 is reported by the same practitioner in the same month."}', 'After consideration of the public comments, we are finalizing the establishment of three new G-codes to be billed as add-on services when the APCM base code (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558) is reported by the same practitioner in the same month: HCPCS code G0568, an add-on code based on CPT code 99492 for an initial month of CoCM services delivered to patients also receiving APCM services, HCPCS code G0569, an add-on code based on CPT code 99493 for CoCM services delivered to patients also receiving APCM services, and HCPCS code G0570, an add-on code for general behavioral health integration services based on CPT code 99484, and are'),
  ('G0557', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT/HCPCS code G0557 (Advanced Primary Care Management (APCM)) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment, and that list (Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix)) is carried into the finalized definition at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) for performance years starting January 1, 2026."}', 'These new HCPCS codes are designed to allow for the payment of services that, when reported as standalone services, are currently included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment when furnished in conjunction with APCM services: BHI (CPT codes 99484, 99492, 99493 and 99494), CoCM (HCPCS code G2214), and APCM (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558)'),
  ('G0558', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0558 (Advanced Primary Care Management) is finalized as a base code for the new behavioral health integration add-on codes G0568, G0569, and G0570, which may be billed when G0558 is reported by the same practitioner in the same month."}', 'After consideration of the public comments, we are finalizing the establishment of three new G-codes to be billed as add-on services when the APCM base code (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558) is reported by the same practitioner in the same month: HCPCS code G0568, an add-on code based on CPT code 99492 for an initial month of CoCM services delivered to patients also receiving APCM services, HCPCS code G0569, an add-on code based on CPT code 99493 for CoCM services delivered to patients also receiving APCM services, and HCPCS code G0570, an add-on code for general behavioral health integration services based on CPT code 99484, and are'),
  ('G0558', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT/HCPCS code G0558 (Advanced Primary Care Management (APCM)) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment, and that list (Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix)) is carried into the finalized definition at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) for performance years starting January 1, 2026."}', 'These new HCPCS codes are designed to allow for the payment of services that, when reported as standalone services, are currently included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment when furnished in conjunction with APCM services: BHI (CPT codes 99484, 99492, 99493 and 99494), CoCM (HCPCS code G2214), and APCM (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558)'),
  ('G0559', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS add-on code G0559, finalized in the CY 2025 PFS final rule, is billed for post-operative care services furnished by a practitioner other than the one who performed the surgical procedure (or another practitioner in the same group practice), reflecting the time and resources of post-operative follow-up visits by practitioners not involved in the surgery."}', 'For CY 2025, we also finalized a new add-on code, HCPCS code G0559, for post-operative care services furnished by a practitioner other than the one who performed the surgical procedure (or another practitioner in the same group practice).'),
  ('G0560', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G0560 (safety planning interventions) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0560 (code for safety planning interventions).'),
  ('G0561', 'covered', 'varies', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0561 (tympanostomy tube delivery device add-on billed with CPT 69433) remains contractor priced for CY 2026; CMS finalized maintaining contractor pricing rather than establishing national pricing, pending more data on the code''s use."}', 'Therefore, we are finalizing to maintain contractor pricing for HCPCS code G0561.'),
  ('G0568', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: for CY 2026, RHCs and FQHCs furnishing Advanced Primary Care Management (APCM) services may report add-on HCPCS code G0568 when they integrate behavioral health (BHI/CoCM) services with APCM. The add-on codes are paid separately from the RHC AIR and FQHC PPS based on the PFS national non-facility payment rate."}', 'may report HCPCS code G0568, G0569, or G0570 when they'),
  ('G0568', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0568 (proposed as GPCM1, describing initial-month psychiatric Collaborative Care Model (CoCM) services furnished as an add-on to Advanced Primary Care Management (APCM)) is finalized and added to the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment at 42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x), for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed the revised definition of primary care services used for assignment for the performance year starting on January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years in a new provision of the Shared Savings Program at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) to include the list of HCPCS and CPT codes specified at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix), as well as the following additions: Enhanced Care Model Management Services (HCPCS codes (GPCM1, GPCM2, and GPCM3 which are being finalized as G0568, G0569, and G0570, respectively)'),
  ('G0568', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0568 has no time-based requirement: the counting of minutes is not required when billed in conjunction with an APCM base code (HCPCS G0556, G0557, or G0558), although the care delivered must still be documented in the medical record."}', 'are introduced, we continue to believe that removing the time-based requirements for HCPCS codes G0568, G0569, and G0570 when billed in conjunction with an APCM base code (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558) will ultimately reduce administrative burden, as it aligns the documentation requirements of the APCM codes with the add-on codes. The time-based requirements for CPT codes 99492, 99493, and 99484 remain in the instance these CPT codes are billed on a standalone basis, outside of the provision of APCM services.'),
  ('G0568', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0568 is considered a designated care management service under 42 CFR 410.26(b)(5) and, as such, may be provided by auxiliary personnel under the general supervision of the billing practitioner."}', 'patients. These proposed optional add-on codes for APCM services would be considered a ``designated care management service'''' at Sec. 410.26(b)(5) and, as such, could be provided by auxiliary personnel under the general supervision of the billing practitioner. In the CY'),
  ('G0569', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: for CY 2026, RHCs and FQHCs furnishing Advanced Primary Care Management (APCM) services may report add-on HCPCS code G0569 when they integrate behavioral health (BHI/CoCM) services with APCM. The add-on codes are paid separately from the RHC AIR and FQHC PPS based on the PFS national non-facility payment rate."}', 'may report HCPCS code G0568, G0569, or G0570 when they'),
  ('G0569', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0569 (proposed as GPCM2, describing subsequent-month psychiatric Collaborative Care Model (CoCM) services furnished as an add-on to Advanced Primary Care Management (APCM)) is finalized and added to the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment at 42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x), for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed the revised definition of primary care services used for assignment for the performance year starting on January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years in a new provision of the Shared Savings Program at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) to include the list of HCPCS and CPT codes specified at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix), as well as the following additions: Enhanced Care Model Management Services (HCPCS codes (GPCM1, GPCM2, and GPCM3 which are being finalized as G0568, G0569, and G0570, respectively)'),
  ('G0569', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0569 has no time-based requirement: the counting of minutes is not required when billed in conjunction with an APCM base code (HCPCS G0556, G0557, or G0558), although the care delivered must still be documented in the medical record."}', 'are introduced, we continue to believe that removing the time-based requirements for HCPCS codes G0568, G0569, and G0570 when billed in conjunction with an APCM base code (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558) will ultimately reduce administrative burden, as it aligns the documentation requirements of the APCM codes with the add-on codes. The time-based requirements for CPT codes 99492, 99493, and 99484 remain in the instance these CPT codes are billed on a standalone basis, outside of the provision of APCM services.'),
  ('G0569', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0569 is considered a designated care management service under 42 CFR 410.26(b)(5) and, as such, may be provided by auxiliary personnel under the general supervision of the billing practitioner."}', 'patients. These proposed optional add-on codes for APCM services would be considered a ``designated care management service'''' at Sec. 410.26(b)(5) and, as such, could be provided by auxiliary personnel under the general supervision of the billing practitioner. In the CY'),
  ('G0570', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: for CY 2026, RHCs and FQHCs furnishing Advanced Primary Care Management (APCM) services may report add-on HCPCS code G0570 when they integrate behavioral health (BHI/CoCM) services with APCM. The add-on codes are paid separately from the RHC AIR and FQHC PPS based on the PFS national non-facility payment rate."}', 'may report HCPCS code G0568, G0569, or G0570 when they'),
  ('G0570', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0570 (proposed as GPCM3, describing general behavioral health integration (BHI) services furnished as an add-on to Advanced Primary Care Management (APCM)) is finalized and added to the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment at 42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x), for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years."}', 'After consideration of public comments, we are finalizing as proposed the revised definition of primary care services used for assignment for the performance year starting on January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years in a new provision of the Shared Savings Program at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) to include the list of HCPCS and CPT codes specified at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix), as well as the following additions: Enhanced Care Model Management Services (HCPCS codes (GPCM1, GPCM2, and GPCM3 which are being finalized as G0568, G0569, and G0570, respectively)'),
  ('G0570', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0570 has no time-based requirement: the counting of minutes is not required when billed in conjunction with an APCM base code (HCPCS G0556, G0557, or G0558), although the care delivered must still be documented in the medical record."}', 'are introduced, we continue to believe that removing the time-based requirements for HCPCS codes G0568, G0569, and G0570 when billed in conjunction with an APCM base code (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558) will ultimately reduce administrative burden, as it aligns the documentation requirements of the APCM codes with the add-on codes. The time-based requirements for CPT codes 99492, 99493, and 99484 remain in the instance these CPT codes are billed on a standalone basis, outside of the provision of APCM services.'),
  ('G0570', 'provider_taxonomy_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G0570 is considered a designated care management service under 42 CFR 410.26(b)(5) and, as such, may be provided by auxiliary personnel under the general supervision of the billing practitioner."}', 'patients. These proposed optional add-on codes for APCM services would be considered a ``designated care management service'''' at Sec. 410.26(b)(5) and, as such, could be provided by auxiliary personnel under the general supervision of the billing practitioner. In the CY'),
  ('G0571', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized creation of new add-on HCPCS code G0571 (intraoperative nerve(s) cryoablation for post-surgical pain relief), to be billed in addition to a primary surgical procedure to account for the additional time and resources of cryoablation. Valuation is crosswalked to CPT 64645 (25 minutes intra-service time, work RVU 1.39); the service is furnished only in the facility setting, so no direct PE inputs were finalized."}', 'we are finalizing the creation of a new add-on G code, HCPCS code G0571 (Intraoperative nerve(s) cryoablation for post-surgical pain relief (list separately in addition to code for primary service)) to be billed with a surgical procedure to account for additional time and resources required to perform cryoablation.'),
  ('G2010', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: beginning January 1, 2026, RHCs and FQHCs furnishing remote evaluation services must report HCPCS code G2010 (in place of unbundled HCPCS G0071) to receive separate payment, paid at the national non-facility PFS payment rate when the code is on an RHC or FQHC claim, alone or with other payable services."}', 'must report HCPCS codes G2010, G2250, and CPT'),
  ('G2012', 'covered', 'not_covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS code G2012 (brief communication technology-based service, e.g., virtual check-in) was terminated effective December 31, 2024, and replaced by CPT code 98016; beginning January 1, 2025, CPT 98016 is used for purposes of computing the HCPCS G0071 payment rate for RHCs and FQHCs."}', 'G2012 was terminated effective December 31, 2024.'),
  ('G2025', 'telehealth_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: RHCs and FQHCs will continue to be paid for medical (non-behavioral health) visit services furnished via telecommunications technology, including audio-only, by reporting HCPCS code G2025 through December 31, 2026, per 42 CFR 405.2464(g). Payment is based on the average amount for all Medicare telehealth services paid under the PFS, weighted by volume."}', 'G2025 through December 31, 2026 in accordance with Sec. 405.2464(g).'),
  ('G2058', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G2058 (non-complex chronic care management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G2058 (code for non-complex chronic care management).'),
  ('G2064', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G2064 (principal care management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G2064 and G2065 (codes for principal care management'),
  ('G2065', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G2065 (principal care management services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G2064 and G2065 (codes for principal care management'),
  ('G2086', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G2086 (office-based opioid use disorder services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G2086, G2087, and G2088 (codes for office-based opioid use'),
  ('G2087', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G2087 (office-based opioid use disorder services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G2086, G2087, and G2088 (codes for office-based opioid use'),
  ('G2088', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G2088 (office-based opioid use disorder services) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G2086, G2087, and G2088 (codes for office-based opioid use'),
  ('G2211', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Finalized for CY 2026: HCPCS code G2211 (visit complexity add-on) may be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visit code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350), in addition to office/outpatient E/M visits; the code descriptor is refined accordingly."}', 'After reviewing all the comments, we are finalizing as proposed, to allow HCPCS code G2211 to be billed as an add-on code with the home or residence E/M visits code family (CPT codes 99341, 99342, 99344, 99345, 99347, 99348, 99349, 99350). We are also finalizing refinement of the'),
  ('G2211', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G2211 (visit complexity inherent to evaluation and management services add-on) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G2211 (code for visit complexity inherent to evaluation and'),
  ('G2212', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G2212 (prolonged office or other outpatient E/M visit) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G0317, G0318, and G2212 (codes for prolonged office or other'),
  ('G2214', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CPT/HCPCS code G2214 (psychiatric collaborative care management (CoCM)) is included in the Shared Savings Program definition of primary care services used for beneficiary assignment, and that list (Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(ix)) is carried into the finalized definition at Sec. 425.400(c)(1)(x) for performance years starting January 1, 2026."}', 'These new HCPCS codes are designed to allow for the payment of services that, when reported as standalone services, are currently included in the definition of primary care services used for purposes of assignment when furnished in conjunction with APCM services: BHI (CPT codes 99484, 99492, 99493 and 99494), CoCM (HCPCS code G2214), and APCM (HCPCS codes G0556, G0557, and G0558)'),
  ('G2250', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"Finalized: beginning January 1, 2026, HCPCS code G2250 (remote assessment of recorded video/images by certain non-physician practitioners) is billable for separate payment when furnished in an RHC or FQHC; RHCs and FQHCs must report it (in place of unbundled HCPCS G0071), paid at the national non-facility PFS payment rate."}', 'must report HCPCS codes G2010, G2250, and CPT'),
  ('G2252', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G2252 (virtual check-in) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G2012 and G2252 (codes for virtual check-in).'),
  ('G3002', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G3002 (chronic pain management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G3002 and G3003 (codes for chronic pain management).'),
  ('G3003', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS G3003 (chronic pain management) is finalized as a primary care service code used for beneficiary assignment under the Medicare Shared Savings Program for the performance year starting January 1, 2026, and subsequent performance years (42 CFR 425.400(c)(1)(x))."}', 'G3002 and G3003 (codes for chronic pain management).'),
  ('G9871', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized new HCPCS code G9871 (behavioral counseling for diabetes prevention, online, 60 minutes) to pay for Medicare Diabetes Prevention Program (MDPP) sessions delivered via the asynchronous Online modality during the Online delivery period, January 1, 2026 through December 31, 2029."}', 'We believe the proposed payment rate for G9871 appropriately reflects the value and costs associated with Online delivery at this time. Therefore, we are finalizing the proposed changes to Sec. 414.84 (c)(3) to indicate payment for Online delivery, including the inclusion of a new HCPCS G-code, G9871.'),
  ('G9871', 'documentation_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"To qualify for payment for an Online MDPP session (G9871), live Coach interaction must occur between the MDPP beneficiary and Coach during weeks when the beneficiary engaged with content, and suppliers may not use AI or machine learning to replace live Coach interaction. CMS finalized 42 CFR 410.79(f) as proposed."}', 'Live Coach interaction must occur between MDPP beneficiaries and Coaches during the weeks when the beneficiary has engaged with content to qualify for payment. MDPP suppliers may not use AI or Machine Learning (ML) to replace Live Coach interaction.'),
  ('G9871', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"MDPP sessions delivered Online (billed with G9871) must follow the finalized session structure to qualify for payment: up to 22 sessions over 12 months, with 16 core sessions delivered weekly (no more than one per week) over the first 6 months, followed by one core maintenance session per month during months 7 through 12."}', 'MDPP suppliers must adhere to the established session structure described at Sec. 424.205(c)(10)(i) to qualify for payment for MDPP sessions. Regardless of delivery modality, MDPP sessions structure consists of up to 22 intensive sessions furnished over 12 months, which includes 16 core sessions delivered weekly over 6 months followed by core maintenance sessions delivered monthly in the following 6 months.'),
  ('G9871', 'modifier_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized revisions at redesignated 42 CFR 414.84(c)(5) adding G9871 (MDPP behavioral counseling for diabetes prevention, online, 60 minutes) to the same-day make-up session rule: CPT Modifier 76 must be appended to any claim for G9871 to identify an MDPP make-up session held on the same day as a regularly scheduled MDPP session."}', 'We are revising this language to include the new G-code for Online delivery, G9871 (Behavioral counseling for diabetes prevention, online, 60 minutes), among the HCPCS codes for same-day make-up sessions'),
  ('G9871', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"MDPP suppliers may not mix delivery modalities for an individual beneficiary: Online sessions billed with G9871 may not be combined with in-person (G9886) or distance learning (G9887) sessions for the same beneficiary during the Online delivery period (through December 31, 2029). The Set of MDPP services must be delivered fully synchronously or fully asynchronously."}', 'we are finalizing the proposal at Sec. 410.79(f)(2)(i)(C) that MDPP suppliers may not mix delivery modalities by billing for a combination of Online, In-Person, and Distance learning sessions during the Online delivery period.'),
  ('G9880', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"Under the finalized CY 2026 MDPP payment structure, the performance payment for achieving 5 percent weight loss from baseline weight (HCPCS G9880) remains the same regardless of MDPP delivery modality (in-person, distance learning, or Online)."}', 'performance payments for 5 percent weight loss achieved from baseline weight (G9880) and 9 percent weight loss achieved from baseline weight (G9881) will remain the same'),
  ('G9881', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"Under the finalized CY 2026 MDPP payment structure, the performance payment for achieving 9 percent weight loss from baseline weight (HCPCS G9881) remains the same regardless of MDPP delivery modality (in-person, distance learning, or Online)."}', 'performance payments for 5 percent weight loss achieved from baseline weight (G9880) and 9 percent weight loss achieved from baseline weight (G9881) will remain the same'),
  ('G9886', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"MDPP in-person sessions (billed with G9886) must follow the finalized session structure to qualify for payment: up to 22 sessions over 12 months, with 16 core sessions delivered weekly (no more than one per week) over the first 6 months, followed by one core maintenance session per month during months 7 through 12."}', 'MDPP suppliers must adhere to the established session structure described at Sec. 424.205(c)(10)(i) to qualify for payment for MDPP sessions. Regardless of delivery modality, MDPP sessions structure consists of up to 22 intensive sessions furnished over 12 months, which includes 16 core sessions delivered weekly over 6 months followed by core maintenance sessions delivered monthly in the following 6 months.'),
  ('G9886', 'modifier_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that CPT Modifier 76 (repeat services by same physician) must be appended to any claim for G9886 (MDPP behavioral counseling for diabetes prevention, in-person, group, 60 minutes) to identify an MDPP make-up session held on the same day as a regularly scheduled MDPP session."}', '``Current Procedural Terminology (CPT) Modifier 76 (repeat services by same physician) must be appended to any claim for G9886, G9887, or G9871 to identify a MDPP make-up session that was held on the same day as a regularly scheduled MDPP session.'''''),
  ('G9886', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"For each MDPP beneficiary, suppliers must bill either synchronous session codes G9886 and/or G9887, or Online code G9871; G9886 (behavioral counseling for diabetes prevention, in-person, group, 60 minutes) may not be billed in combination with G9871 Online sessions for the same beneficiary during the Online delivery period (through December 31, 2029)."}', 'For each beneficiary, MDPP suppliers must either bill claims with G9886, G9887, a combination of G9886 and G9887, or G9871.'),
  ('G9887', 'frequency_limit', 'covered', '{"answer":"MDPP distance learning sessions (billed with G9887) must follow the finalized session structure to qualify for payment: up to 22 sessions over 12 months, with 16 core sessions delivered weekly (no more than one per week) over the first 6 months, followed by one core maintenance session per month during months 7 through 12."}', 'MDPP suppliers must adhere to the established session structure described at Sec. 424.205(c)(10)(i) to qualify for payment for MDPP sessions. Regardless of delivery modality, MDPP sessions structure consists of up to 22 intensive sessions furnished over 12 months, which includes 16 core sessions delivered weekly over 6 months followed by core maintenance sessions delivered monthly in the following 6 months.'),
  ('G9887', 'modifier_required', 'covered', '{"answer":"CMS finalized that CPT Modifier 76 (repeat services by same physician) must be appended to any claim for G9887 (MDPP behavioral counseling for diabetes prevention, distance learning, group, 60 minutes) to identify an MDPP make-up session held on the same day as a regularly scheduled MDPP session."}', '``Current Procedural Terminology (CPT) Modifier 76 (repeat services by same physician) must be appended to any claim for G9886, G9887, or G9871 to identify a MDPP make-up session that was held on the same day as a regularly scheduled MDPP session.'''''),
  ('G9887', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"For each MDPP beneficiary, suppliers must bill either synchronous session codes G9886 and/or G9887, or Online code G9871; G9887 (behavioral counseling for diabetes prevention, distance learning, 60 minutes) may not be billed in combination with G9871 Online sessions for the same beneficiary during the Online delivery period (through December 31, 2029)."}', 'For each beneficiary, MDPP suppliers must either bill claims with G9886, G9887, a combination of G9886 and G9887, or G9871.'),
  ('J2820', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized no change to the discarded drug refund applicable percentage for HCPCS J2820 (Leukine, sargramostim): the manufacturer''s request for a 72 percent applicable percentage was denied, so J2820 remains subject to the standard 10 percent applicable percentage. CMS found discard rates of only 1.2 to 3.8 percent in 2018-2024 claims data, below the 10 percent threshold."}', 'Leukine[supreg] (J2820) ranged from 1.2 percent to 3.8 percent'),
  ('Q3014', 'telehealth_allowed', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS finalized the Medicare telehealth originating site facility fee payment amount for HCPCS code Q3014 at $31.85, reflecting the 2.7 percent Medicare Economic Index (MEI) increase for CY 2026; the proposal was finalized as proposed after consideration of public comments."}', 'HCPCS code Q3014 (Telehealth originating site facility fee) is $31.85.'),
  ('Q3014', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, the payment amount for HCPCS Q3014 (telehealth originating site facility fee) is $31.85, reflecting the 2.7 percent Medicare Economic Index (MEI) increase; CMS finalized the update as proposed."}', 'Therefore, for CY 2026, the payment amount for HCPCS code Q3014 (Telehealth originating site facility fee) is $31.85.'),
  ('Q4107', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4107 is finalized as an add-on code with global indicator ZZZ (0 MP RVUs), reportable only together with a CPT skin substitute application base code (for example, CPT 15271) rather than as a standalone service."}', 'we are finalizing the conversion of all skin substitute products codes to add-on codes with an indicator of ZZZ.'),
  ('Q4107', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS Q4107 is a covered skin substitute product that, starting January 1, 2026, is paid separately as an incident-to supply in both non-facility and hospital outpatient settings. For CY 2026, CMS finalized rates for Q4107 using the FDA-category groupings from the proposed rule; prospectively, CMS will designate Q4107 to the FDA regulatory category grouping suggested by commenters."}', 'After careful consideration of the comments, for CY 2026 we are finalizing rates consistent with the groupings illustrated in the proposed rule in the interest of transparency and consistency. Prospectively, however, we will designate these HCPCS to the groupings suggested by commenters.'),
  ('Q4107', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4107 is paid at the finalized single CY 2026 payment rate of $127.28 per square centimeter (prior to geographic adjustment), the rate that applies to all skin substitute products in the three FDA regulatory categories (PMA, 510(k), and 361 HCT/P)."}', 'finalizing a final payment rate for CY 2026 of $127.28/cm\2\.'),
  ('Q4108', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4108 is finalized as an add-on code with global indicator ZZZ (0 MP RVUs), reportable only together with a CPT skin substitute application base code (for example, CPT 15271) rather than as a standalone service."}', 'we are finalizing the conversion of all skin substitute products codes to add-on codes with an indicator of ZZZ.'),
  ('Q4108', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS Q4108 is a covered skin substitute product that, starting January 1, 2026, is paid separately as an incident-to supply in both non-facility and hospital outpatient settings. For CY 2026, CMS finalized rates for Q4108 using the FDA-category groupings from the proposed rule; prospectively, CMS will designate Q4108 to the FDA regulatory category grouping suggested by commenters."}', 'After careful consideration of the comments, for CY 2026 we are finalizing rates consistent with the groupings illustrated in the proposed rule in the interest of transparency and consistency. Prospectively, however, we will designate these HCPCS to the groupings suggested by commenters.'),
  ('Q4108', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4108 is paid at the finalized single CY 2026 payment rate of $127.28 per square centimeter (prior to geographic adjustment), the rate that applies to all skin substitute products in the three FDA regulatory categories (PMA, 510(k), and 361 HCT/P)."}', 'finalizing a final payment rate for CY 2026 of $127.28/cm\2\.'),
  ('Q4116', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4116 is finalized as an add-on code with global indicator ZZZ (0 MP RVUs), reportable only together with a CPT skin substitute application base code (for example, CPT 15271) rather than as a standalone service."}', 'we are finalizing the conversion of all skin substitute products codes to add-on codes with an indicator of ZZZ.'),
  ('Q4116', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS Q4116 is a covered skin substitute product that, starting January 1, 2026, is paid separately as an incident-to supply in both non-facility and hospital outpatient settings. For CY 2026, CMS finalized rates for Q4116 using the FDA-category groupings from the proposed rule; prospectively, CMS will designate Q4116 to the FDA regulatory category grouping suggested by commenters."}', 'After careful consideration of the comments, for CY 2026 we are finalizing rates consistent with the groupings illustrated in the proposed rule in the interest of transparency and consistency. Prospectively, however, we will designate these HCPCS to the groupings suggested by commenters.'),
  ('Q4116', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4116 is paid at the finalized single CY 2026 payment rate of $127.28 per square centimeter (prior to geographic adjustment), the rate that applies to all skin substitute products in the three FDA regulatory categories (PMA, 510(k), and 361 HCT/P)."}', 'finalizing a final payment rate for CY 2026 of $127.28/cm\2\.'),
  ('Q4122', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4122 is finalized as an add-on code with global indicator ZZZ (0 MP RVUs), reportable only together with a CPT skin substitute application base code (for example, CPT 15271) rather than as a standalone service."}', 'we are finalizing the conversion of all skin substitute products codes to add-on codes with an indicator of ZZZ.'),
  ('Q4122', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS Q4122 is a covered skin substitute product that, starting January 1, 2026, is paid separately as an incident-to supply in both non-facility and hospital outpatient settings. For CY 2026, CMS finalized rates for Q4122 using the FDA-category groupings from the proposed rule; prospectively, CMS will designate Q4122 to the FDA regulatory category grouping suggested by commenters."}', 'After careful consideration of the comments, for CY 2026 we are finalizing rates consistent with the groupings illustrated in the proposed rule in the interest of transparency and consistency. Prospectively, however, we will designate these HCPCS to the groupings suggested by commenters.'),
  ('Q4122', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4122 is paid at the finalized single CY 2026 payment rate of $127.28 per square centimeter (prior to geographic adjustment), the rate that applies to all skin substitute products in the three FDA regulatory categories (PMA, 510(k), and 361 HCT/P)."}', 'finalizing a final payment rate for CY 2026 of $127.28/cm\2\.'),
  ('Q4142', 'bundled_with', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4142 is finalized as an add-on code with global indicator ZZZ (0 MP RVUs), reportable only together with a CPT skin substitute application base code (for example, CPT 15271) rather than as a standalone service."}', 'we are finalizing the conversion of all skin substitute products codes to add-on codes with an indicator of ZZZ.'),
  ('Q4142', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS Q4142 is a covered skin substitute product that, starting January 1, 2026, is paid separately as an incident-to supply in both non-facility and hospital outpatient settings. For CY 2026, CMS finalized rates for Q4142 using the FDA-category groupings from the proposed rule; prospectively, CMS will designate Q4142 to the FDA regulatory category grouping suggested by commenters."}', 'After careful consideration of the comments, for CY 2026 we are finalizing rates consistent with the groupings illustrated in the proposed rule in the interest of transparency and consistency. Prospectively, however, we will designate these HCPCS to the groupings suggested by commenters.'),
