  ('Q4297', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS Q4297 is a covered skin substitute product that, starting January 1, 2026, is paid separately as an incident-to supply in both non-facility and hospital outpatient settings. For CY 2026, CMS finalized rates for Q4297 using the FDA-category groupings from the proposed rule; prospectively, CMS will designate Q4297 to the FDA regulatory category grouping suggested by commenters."}', 'After careful consideration of the comments, for CY 2026 we are finalizing rates consistent with the groupings illustrated in the proposed rule in the interest of transparency and consistency. Prospectively, however, we will designate these HCPCS to the groupings suggested by commenters.'),
  ('Q4297', 'units_per_period_max', 'covered', '{"answer":"Skin substitute product HCPCS Q4297 is paid at the finalized single CY 2026 payment rate of $127.28 per square centimeter (prior to geographic adjustment), the rate that applies to all skin substitute products in the three FDA regulatory categories (PMA, 510(k), and 361 HCT/P)."}', 'finalizing a final payment rate for CY 2026 of $127.28/cm\2\.'),
  ('Q4431', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS Q4431 (Unlisted PMA skin substitute product) is the not-otherwise-classified code used for a PMA-approved skin substitute product before a product-specific HCPCS code is assigned; the Medicare MACs assign the appropriate payment based on the product''s FDA regulatory category."}', 'Before a code is assigned, not otherwise classified (NOC) HCPCS codes Q4431 (Unlisted PMA skin substitute product), Q4432 (Unlisted 510(k) skin substitute product), and Q4433 (Unlisted 361 HCT/P skin substitute product) would be used and the CMS MACs would assign the appropriate payment based on the product''s FDA regulatory category.'),
  ('Q4432', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS Q4432 (Unlisted 510(k) skin substitute product) is the not-otherwise-classified code used for a 510(k)-cleared skin substitute product before a product-specific HCPCS code is assigned; the Medicare MACs assign the appropriate payment based on the product''s FDA regulatory category."}', 'Before a code is assigned, not otherwise classified (NOC) HCPCS codes Q4431 (Unlisted PMA skin substitute product), Q4432 (Unlisted 510(k) skin substitute product), and Q4433 (Unlisted 361 HCT/P skin substitute product) would be used and the CMS MACs would assign the appropriate payment based on the product''s FDA regulatory category.'),
  ('Q4433', 'covered', 'covered', '{"answer":"HCPCS Q4433 (Unlisted 361 HCT/P skin substitute product) is the not-otherwise-classified code used for a 361 HCT/P skin substitute product before a product-specific HCPCS code is assigned; the Medicare MACs assign the appropriate payment based on the product''s FDA regulatory category."}', 'Before a code is assigned, not otherwise classified (NOC) HCPCS codes Q4431 (Unlisted PMA skin substitute product), Q4432 (Unlisted 510(k) skin substitute product), and Q4433 (Unlisted 361 HCT/P skin substitute product) would be used and the CMS MACs would assign the appropriate payment based on the product''s FDA regulatory category.'),
  ('R0070', 'covered', 'varies', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS did not establish national pricing for HCPCS code R0070 (transportation of portable x-ray equipment and personnel to home or nursing home, per trip, one patient seen); the code remains contractor priced by the MACs (observed at roughly $215 to $230 per service), with commenter concerns to inform any future national rate."}', 'the concerns raised by commenters to help inform any establishment of a'),
  ('R0075', 'covered', 'varies', '{"answer":"For CY 2026, CMS did not establish national pricing for HCPCS code R0075 (transportation of portable x-ray equipment and personnel to home or nursing home, per trip, more than one patient seen); the code remains contractor priced by the MACs (observed at roughly $80 to $90 per service), with commenter concerns to inform any future national rate."}', 'the concerns raised by commenters to help inform any establishment of a');
